Simon Ivermee on his lunch break at his work place, tools in background, veneer shop, Thomas Glenister's chair factory. Notes from Albert Ivermee chair-worker and photographer, taken for new works brochure

Dining room of the Red Lion Hotel, High St, High Wycombe. about Aug 1934
Interior of Red Lion Showing dining room with tables set, moulded plaster work on ceiling and walls

Interior of band saw mill showing bandsaw (made by Danckaert) at Thomas Glenister's chair factory, Bellfield Rd, High Wycombe. about 1972
Interior of band saw mill showing bandsaw made by Danckaert at Thomas Glenister's chair factory. Closer view of MHW01469 and MHW01403. Notes and photograph by Albert Ivermee.

Paul Cander and co-worker, Thomas Glenister's chair factory, Temple End, High Wycombe. 1971
Paul Cander and co-worker, Thomas Glenister's chair factory. Notes from Albert Ivermee chair-worker and photographer, taken for new works brochure

From NE, a view of the buildings, before extension eastward, at Godstowe School, Amersham Rd, High Wycombe. about 1907
Showing N. side of Godstowe School buildings before they were extended to the East. Another building, possibly a class room standing at right angles

Looking east from close to the junction with Kings road, a view along London Rd, Wycombe Marsh. 1930s
Further along from RHW01208

A large floor-mounted steam-driven double cylinder engine in the 1891 boiler house of Thomas Glenister's factory, Bellfield Rd, High Wycombe. about 1990
A large floor mounted steam driven double cylinder engine housed in the 1891 boiler house of the factory of Thomas Glenister. It is connected to a large electric generator by a shaft. Broom resting against it.

From NE, a view of the grounds and rear of Godstowe School, Amersham Rd, High Wycombe. July 1925
Back view of Godstowe School buildings and school field

Viewed through the arches of the Guildhall, the Black Boy Inn and premises in Church St, High Wycombe. about 1930
Photo taken through arches of Guildhall showing Black Boy Inn, G.E. Stevens[corn dealer] number 22 Church St, W. McIlroy[drapers]

Steel work benches and bending machine in the veneer shop at Thomas Glenister's chair factory, Bellfield Rd, High Wycombe. about 1972
Veneer shop at Thomas Glenister's chair factory showing steel work benches and bending machine. Doors already bent stacked on floor. Notes and photograph by Albert Ivermee.

Looking E. a view of traffic on the A40 towards the Hatters Lane/London Rd junction, Wycombe Marsh. July 1990
Looking E. along London Rd, N. side traffic sign, houses in Pinions Rd, houses on London Rd, offices in Hatters Lane, Express Dairy milk float

Paul Cander gluing frames before paper skin is applied, Thomas Glenister's chair factory, Temple End, High Wycombe. 1971
Paul Cander gluing frames before paper skin is applied, visible are press patters(?), jointer and drum sander, Thomas Glenister's chair factory. Notes from Albert Ivermee chair-worker and photographer, taken for new works brochure

Chair framers at their benches in the factory of Thomas Glenister in Temple End, High Wycombe. 1907
Chair framers at their benches in factory of Thomas Glenister. This shows a large shop with plenty of room at the benches and a good gangway between the stock and the benches. Also chair frames with carved backs, and tools.

The Red Lion public house, viewed looking N.W. towards junction of Cock Lane and London Rd, Wycombe Marsh. July 1990
Red Lion public house at junction of London Rd and Cock Lane

Looking E, the interior of empty upholstery workshop in Glenister's chair factory, Bellfield Rd, High Wycombe. about 1990
Interior of empty upholstery workshop in Glenister's chair factory. Upper storey, windows on either side, those on right blocked up, brick walls, green door at far end on left. Another view on MHW01461

A view of part of a machine, a floor-mounted steam-driven double cylinder engine at Glenister's factory, Bellfield Rd, High Wycombe. about 1990
A view of part of machine in MHW01435, a floor mounted steam driven double cylinder engine, connected to a large electric generator by a shaft in Thomas Glenister's chair factory.

Girls working in Science classroom, County High School, Benjamin Rd, High Wycombe. about 1907
Girls working in Science classroom, County High School

View looking W towards junction of Abbey Barn Rd and London Rd, Wycombe Marsh. July 1990
W. side Abbey Barn Rd cottages, renovated building, sign Red Lion House New Office Development To Let, Cranford Estates Construction Ltd, Wycombe Marsh Paper Mills in background and chimney

mentions.ne_span: Red Lion House New Office Development

text:
Ballroom of Red Lion Hotel, High St, High Wycombe. about Aug 1934
Interior of Red Lion Hotel showing ballroom with chairs and piano, moulded plaster work on ceiling.

Girls of County High School performing a scene from Midsummer Night's Dream, Benjamin Rd, High Wycombe. Dec 1909
Girls of County High School performing a scene from Midsummer Night's Dream

Maker's plate Davey Paxman and Co.Ltd. Makers Colchester on machine in MHW01435, Glenister's factory, Bellfield Rd High Wycombe about 1990
Maker's plate Davey Paxman and Co. Ltd. Makers Colchester on machine in MHW01435, a floor mounted steam driven double cylinder engine in Thomas Glenister's chair factory.

From beyond the junction with Lucas Rd, a view looking S into the valley down Amersham Hill, High Wycombe. Sept 1991
Looking S. showing houses and trees on both sides, E. side school sign, W. side estate agents sign Raffety Buckland, buildings and lands of Wycombe Abbey School in the distance

Seen from the North, the east-facing front of the 'Out Houses', used as boarding houses at Wycombe Abbey School, Marlow Hill, High Wycombe. about 1900
Out houses, used as boarding houses, Wycombe Abbey School, viewed from North showing East facing front, in use by 1900. These two may be Cambell and Airlie.

Looking N.W. a view of the former Thames Valley bus garage at junction of Micklefield Rd/London Rd, Wycombe Marsh. July 1990
London Rd showing N. side junction with Micklefield Rd, SMC Tyres and Exhausts (511 London Rd) Heating and Plumbing Supplies shop, S. side site of Wycombe Marsh Paper Mills

Viewed from N, the stone laying ceremony for additional buildings to Wycombe High School, Benjamin Rd, High Wycombe. July 1911
Stone laying ceremony for additional buildings to Wycombe High School, later known as Lady Verney School. The new wing, completed in 1912, was used for Cookery, Laundry and Housewifery. The Headmistress at the time was Miss Mary Christie, but she was unable to be present for the ceremony. 
The foundation stone was laid by the Chairman of the Governors, Alderman Deacon JP CC, on Monday July 31st 1911. The man standing behind the stone is Mr J.T.Harris, whose company built the new wing.

Looking E, the interior of empty upholstery workshop in Glenister's chair factory, Bellfield Rd, High Wycombe. about 1990
Interior of empty upholstery workshop in Glenister's chair factory. Upper storey with windows on either side, those on right blocked up, brick walls, green door at far end on left. Another view on MHW01462

Portrait of Ellen (Nell) Glenister seated and Mary Glenister standing, possibly in garden of Glenister's house, Temple End, High Wycombe. about 1900
Portrait of Nell Glenister (Ellen) seated and Mary Glenister standing. Nell Glenister was daughter of Ellen Glenister born 1863, and Frederick James Bunyan Mullett. Mary Griffin Glenister, born 1887, married William Robert Butler.

Girls boating on the Lake in the grounds of Wycombe Abbey School, Marlow Hill, High Wycombe. about 1900
Girls boating on the Lake in Wycombe Abbey School. Lake crossed by wooden footbridge, surrounded by trees, lawns and gravel paths.

View from S.W.of ground floor window of studio of Edward Sweetland, 20a High St, High Wycombe. about 1905
View of ground floor window of studio of Edward Sweetland number 20a High St, showing portraits and views. On E. side part of number 20(b) with sign Everetts Polishes - probably Busby's Boot shop

Looking N. a view of Micklefield Rd from S of the railway bridge to junction with London Rd, Wycombe Marsh. July 1990
Micklefield Rd from junction with London Rd to railway bridge showing W. side SMC Tyres and Exhausts and houses, E. side car park and houses

A portable steam engine drives a threshing machine at harvest, along with a cart from the chair factory of Thomas Glenister in use. location unknown. about 1890
A cart from the chair factory of Thomas Glenister in use during harvest. A portable steam engine drives threshing machine, while a horse feeds and boys look on.

Seen from S, the ground floor display window at the premises of Edward Sweetland, 20a High St, High Wycombe. about 1905
View of ground floor window of the premises of Edward Sweetland, number 20a High St. On the W. side offices of South Bucks Free Press.

From close to the junction with Kings Road, a view looking N.W. along N. side of London Rd, Wycombe Marsh. July 1990
N. side of London Rd showing offices to let, advertisement for Vauxhall cars and M.O.T. tests

St Anne's Church and Wycombe Marsh Paper Mills viewed towards NW from junction of Abbey Barn Rd/London Rd, Wycombe Marsh. July 1990
N. side London Rd. St Anne's Church and flats behind, S. side junction of Abbey Barn Rd and London Rd, on W. corner sign Red Lion House New Office Development To Let, Wycombe Marsh Paper Mills Ltd

Seen from the NE, a view of some of the buildings of Wycombe High School, Benjamin Road, High Wycombe. Sept 1923
View of block of buildings with small cupola in Wycombe High School, later Known as Lady Verney High School.

Seen from the Northwest, the eastern end of the North-facing front of Wycombe Abbey School and grounds, Marlow Hill, High Wycombe. about 1900
East end of North facing front of Wycombe Abbey School, ivy clad walls and Gothic style door and lower windows. Girls walking in grounds and playing tennis.

View from W of former business premises of Edward Sweetland, Crown Lane, High Wycombe. about 1910
View of former business premises of Edward Sweetland, a three storey house on E. side of Crown Lane prior to junction with Paul's Row. Three steps to door inset between pillars, well proportioned twelve paned windows and parapet. Adjacent on South is the shop of A.E. and H.A. Hole, saddlers and harness makers.

Looking N to King Sq and junction with Abbey Barn Rd, along Beech Rd, Wycombe Marsh. July 1990
Beech Rd showing houses on both sides, war memorial in Kings Sq. and Free Methodist Church, Abbey Barn Rd

Girls of the County High School performing a scene from Midsummer Night's Dream, Benjamin Rd, High Wycombe. Dec 1909
Girls of the County High School performing a scene from Midsummer Night's Dream

A side view of a floor mounted steam driven double cylinder engine at Thomas Glenister's chair factory, Bellfield Rd, High Wycombe. about 1990
A side view of a floor mounted steam driven double cylinder engine at Thomas Glenister's chair factory, made by Davey Paxman and Co. Ltd, Engineers, Colchester, Patent by Lentz. Another view of MHW01405 and MHW01406, housed in 1891 boiler house.

View from S. of ground floor window of studio of Edward Sweetland at The White House, 21 High St, High Wycombe. 1921
View of ground floor window of studio of Edward Sweetland number 21 High St. (a.k.a. The White House) showing portraits.

View looking N.E. towards the junction of Keep Hill Rd, Chestnut Avenue and Bassetsbury Lane. High Wycombe. July 1990
Looking N.E. towards junction of Keep Hill Rd, Chestnut Avenue and Bassetsbury Lane showing housing on E. and on hill beyond

View of inside of engine house showing side view of a single cylinder diesel engine. Glenister's chair factory, Bellfield Rd, High Wycombe. 1991
Showing inside of building, (engine house in MHW01397), side view of single cylinder diesel engine, made by RUSTON, RUSTON and HORNSBY LTD, LINCOLN.

From just before junction with Gordon Rd, a view looking West along London Rd, High Wycombe. July 1990
Looking W. London Rd at junction with Gordon Rd showing N. side Pheasant public house, shops and houses, S. side garage.

Pupils of County High School performing scene from Midsummer Night's Dream, Benjamin Rd, High Wycombe. Dec 1909
Scenes from Midsummer Night's Dream performed by Pupils of the County High School

Interior view of 1891 boiler house with a Marshall's compound stationary steam engine. Glenister's chair factory, Bellfield Rd, High Wycombe. 1991
Inside view of 1891 boiler house with a Marshall's compound stationary steam engine originally used to drive the old belt driven machinery. Shows aperture where main belt from from engine passed through.

From SW, opposite junction with Abbey Barn Rd, a view of St Anne's Church and adjacent premises on the N side of London Rd, Wycombe Marsh. July 1990
Showing N side of London Rd from St Anne's Church, cottages and car showroom.

An aerial view of Wycombe Abbey School and grounds, Wycombe and District memorial Hospital and bus garage, High Wycombe. 1930s?
Aerial view of Wycombe Abbey School and grounds with kitchen garden and lake, Wycombe and District Memorial Hosp. and London Transport Garage, Tom Burt's Hill in background.

Interior view of bandsaw shed, showing bandsaw rack and log carrier, by plank exit door. Glenister's chair factory, Bellfield Rd, High Wycombe. 1991
View of bandsaw, rack and log carrier, from a position by plank exit door (see MHW01395), note bogie for carrying cut planks.

Looking E. towards a right-hand bend, a view along Bassetsbury Lane, High Wycombe. July 1990
Looking E. a view of Bassetsbury La. towards the double bend, house on left

From the East, a view of the front of the Royal Grammar School buildings on Amersham Rd at junction with Hamilton Rd, High Wycombe. about 1950
Front of Royal Grammar School buildings on Amersham Rd built to a design by Arthur Vernon and opened in 1915. Showing school with wings built in 1938 but before front extension which was added in 1962. Newly planted trees and house in Hamilton Rd.

Looking N. a view of the ford across the R. Wye in Beech Rd, Wycombe Marsh. July 1990
Beech Rd with ford over R. Wye, cottages to W. and E.

View of interior of bandsaw shed, bandsaw and band-rack, with uncut log carrier clearly visible. Glenister's chair factory, Bellfield Rd, High Wycombe. 1991
Inside of bandsaw shed, bandsaw and band-rack, with uncut log carrier clearly visible, the bandsaw makers are Danckaert

From S. front of Technical School in Easton St with ruins of Hospital of St John on right, High Wycombe. Feb 1928
Front of Technical School in Easton St with ruins of Hospital of St John on right. Buildings of school designed by Arthur Vernon formally used by Royal Grammar School. Signs on front railings from left, Juvenile Employment Bureau, Junior Day Technical School, High Wycombe Technical Institute Day and Evening Classes, Day Commercial School. Junior Technical School set up in 1920. Commercial School for boys and girls from the age of 13 set up in 1924.

An aerial view from the South, showing Wycombe Abbey School, the grounds, Marlow Hill, High St and Easton St, High Wycombe. about 1928
An aerial view of Wycombe Abbey School, grounds with kitchen garden and lake, and showing Marlow Hill, part of the War Memorial Hospital, Town Hall, Easton St and High St

Sketch by Francis Colmer of demolition of Black Boy Inn, Church St, High Wycombe, Aug 1931
Sketch showing demolition of Black Boy Inn, and adjoining buildings

Looking NE. a view of Marsh Green House and adjoining cottages, Bassetsbury Lane, High Wycombe. July 1990
View of Marsh Green House and adjoining cottages

From E, Jocelyn Woolley and Heather Greenwood at the enquiry desk in the Reference Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. 1990s
Jocelyn Woolley and Heather Greenwood at the enquiry desk in the Reference Library, High Wycombe.

View from SW of red brick house used as offices for Glenister's chair makers, and out buildings, Temple End, High Wycombe. 1991
View of red brick house used as offices for Glenister's chair makers, and out buildings. A two storey building, brick ground floor with weather-boarding to first floor painted blue. Former Police Station on corner of Hughenden Rd and Benjamin Rd in background.

Looking S.W. a view of the Dyke showing the dam and waterfall. The Rye, High Wycombe. July 1990
A view of Dyke showing dam and waterfall

Close-up of stone plaque with date 1896 and initials T.G. on upper storey of building, part of Thomas Glenister's chair factory,Temple End, High Wycombe. about 1990
Stone plaque with date 1896 and initials T.G. on upper storey of red brick building, part of Thomas Glenister's chair factory. Closer image of MHW01398

Copy of an illustration(?) showing the Guildhall and West end of the High St, High Wycombe. 1930s?
Showing Red Lion Hotel, Falcon Hotel and Guildhall

Karen Walton standing by the enquiry desk in the Reference Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. 1990s
Karen Walton standing by the enquiry desk in the Reference Library, High Wycombe.

Photo of an engraving of Wycombe House (Wycombe Abbey) and grounds seen from the South, near Daws Hill Lane, High Wycombe. c1775?
Drawing of Wycombe House, now Wycombe Abbey School, then the house of the Marquis of Lansdown, with horse riders and parish church in background.

View from N.W. of Judith Shakespeare working in the office in the Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. about 1990
Judith Shakespeare working in the Librarian's office in High Wycombe Library. N. side of Town Hall seen through window.

View of Nos 1 and 2, at the western end of the High St, High Wycombe. about 1910
Butler Bros, number 2, (chemist and bookseller), Showing Little Market House and other shops

Looking N.E. from Deangarden Wood a view across the valley to housing N of Wycombe Marsh. July 1990
From Deangarden Wood across valley showing housing in Bank St etc ('Tintown') on N. side London Rd and factory building

A view of the flywheel end of a floor-mounted steam-driven double cylinder engine at Glenister's factory, Bellfield Rd, High Wycombe. about 1990
A view of the flywheel end of a floor-mounted steam-driven double cylinder engine, connected to a large electric generator by a shaft in Thomas Glenister's chair factory.

Jocelyn Woolley answering the telephone and Barbara Mathers looking on in the Library workroom, Queen Victoria Rd. High Wycombe. about 1990s
Jocelyn Woolley answering the telephone and Barbara Mathers looking on in the Library workroom, High Wycombe. A box from Gardner's Books stands on a table.

Looking W, the Dyke along the left of a view of the S. side of the Rye, High Wycombe. July 1990
Dyke and path alongside, grass, crane in background

View possibly of N side of dining room in White House, home of Edward Sweetland photographer, High St, High Wycombe. about 1920
View possibly of N. side of dining room in White House, home of Edward Sweetland photographer, showing furniture including winged armchair and fireplace and half height wooden panelling.

Exterior view of workshops, brick-built ground floor and wood-clad upper floor. Part of Thomas Glenister's chair factory, Temple End, High Wycombe. 1930's?
Exterior view of workshops, part of Thomas Glenister's chair factory. Brick-built ground floor, and wood-clad upper floor

Postcard showing a view of the entrance hall Wycombe Abbey School, High Wycombe. date unknown
Interior of Wycombe Abbey School, entrance hall with American Plaque, Gothic style window and ceiling, table chairs and carpet, picture/hanging over fireplace

Looking W. from opposite junction with Bull Lane, a view of S Side of Oxford St, High Wycombe. about 1899
Showing steam engine and trailer, horse and cart with chairs, shops on S. side

In the Library foyer, a display to commemorate the Golden Jubilee of the accession of Queen Elizabeth II, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. 2002
A display to commemorate the Golden Jubilee of the accession of Queen Elizabeth II in the Library foyer. Displays entitled The Accession and Coronation Addresses of the London County Council, Queen Elizabeth the Queen Mother 4th August 1900 to 30th March 2002, Three Princesses and Royal Style. Another image on RHW01597

View of SW corner of sitting room in White house, home of Edward Sweetland photographer, High St, High Wycombe. about 1920
View of S.W. corner of sitting room in White house, home of Edward Sweetland photographer, showing furniture.

From N, a view of N room of Reference Library, through arch into S room after refurbishment, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. 1990s
View of N. room of Reference Library, through arch into S. room after refurbishment. Showing light grey metal shelving, tables and chairs in light wood, chairs with blue covers and tables with black tops. Painting on back wall of N. room Other views of refurbishment on RHW01557 to 01561

Looking N, a view of numbers 1 to 4 at the west end of the High St, High Wycombe. about 1950
No 1(florist), Wheatsheaf Tobacco Stores, no. 2 Cyril Roberts (photographer), no. 3 Eric Wakefield (travel agent) The Grapes (public house)

In the Library foyer, a display to commemorate the Golden Jubilee of the accession of Queen Elizabeth II, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. 2002
A display to commemorate the Golden Jubilee of the accession of Queen Elizabeth II in the Library foyer. Banner hanging above. Displays entitled Queen's visit to High Wycombe in 1962, The Queen's Image, The Accession and Coronation Addresses of the London County Council and Queen Elizabeth the Queen Mother 4th August 1900 to 30th March 2002. Another image on RHW01598

Photograph of bare trees and cupola of unknown building against a clouded sky. location unknown. date unknown
Photograph of bare trees against a clouded sky, contrasting darkness at ground level with brightness behind clouds. Cupola of unknown building silhouetted amongst trees in right foreground.

Presentation of long service awards by Roy Collis, County Librarian, to Mary Woodward, Gerd Thomson, Janet Long and Jaci Beaven, Aylesbury. about 1994
Presentation of long service awards by Roy Collis, County Librarian, to Mary Woodward, Gerd Thomson, Janet Long and Jaci Beaven. Event possibly in Judges Lodgings, Aylesbury.

From the West, demolition of shops North of Red Cow PH, and interior of shop of F.W. George prior to the building of Tesco. Frogmoor, High Wycombe. 1963
Demolition of shops North of Red Cow public house, and interior of F.W. George, heating engineer in Frogmoor prior to the building of Tesco. Two vehicles one with number MPB551, one 665FOG and name 'Rust-Oleum'

Rob Andrews standing before racks of CDs in the Music Library, Queen Victoria Rd. High Wycombe. Feb 1999
Rob Andrews standing before racks of CDs in display labelled Pop and Rock CDs in the Music Library High Wycombe.

View of newel post carved with initials TG and date 1897, in the house used as offices at Glenister's chair factory, Temple End, High Wycombe. date unknown
View of carved newel post in house used as offices by Glenister chair maker, carved with initials TG and date 1897

View of dining room in White House, home of Edward Sweetland photographer, High St, High Wycombe. about 1920
View of dining room in White House, home of Edward Sweetland photographer, showing half height wooden panelling and photograph of young woman.

Presentation of long-service awards to Janet Long, Jaci Beaven and Mary Woodward, Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. c1994
Presentation of long-service awards to Janet Long, Jaci Beaven and Mary Woodward. Similar image on RHW01570 and 01571.

Heather Greenwood and Karen Walton working at the enquiry desk in the Reference Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. about 1990
Heather Greenwood and Karen Walton working at the enquiry desk in the Reference Library, High Wycombe.

From path above Back Lane (Bassetsbury Lane), a view NE across the valley to Hatters Lane, High Wycombe. July 1990
View from path above Back Lane, view across valley to Hatters La and housing

A floor mounted Davey-Paxman steam-driven double cylinder engine housed in the 1891 boiler house. Glenister's chair factory, Bellfield Rd, High Wycombe. 1991
A floor-mounted Davey-Paxman steam-driven double cylinder engine, housed in the 1891 boiler house, it is connected to a large electric generator by a shaft, the generator was made by CROMPTON. Another view on MHW01405

View of NW corner of sitting room in White House, home of Edward Sweetland photographer, High St, High Wycombe. about 1920
View of N.W. corner of sitting room in White House home of Edward Sweetland photographer, showing furniture and piano.

Seen from SE, a view of the interior of the Reference Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. early 1990s
View of interior of Reference Library in early 1990s showing shelving, tables and checking in desk.

Sue Jones working in the staff area of the Lending Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. about the 1990s.
Sue Jones working in the staff area of the Lending Library next to the work room. To the right a computer for public use with a poster on How to use a CD Rom. In the foreground a trolley with Paperback Clearance Sale.

From the West, a view of the shop of F.W.George Ltd. in early stages of demolition prior to the building of Tesco. Frogmoor, High Wycombe. 1963
Shop of F.W.George Ltd. heating engineers and ironmonger in Frogmoor in early stages of demolition prior to the building of Tesco. Shop to right nearly demolished. Lorry in foreground, number MPB551

From S, a view of N room of Reference Library after refurbishment, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. 1990s
View of N. room of Reference Library, photograph taken towards entrance. Showing Reference Library after refurbishment with light grey metal shelving, tables and chairs in light wood, chairs with blue covers and tables with black tops. Another view of RHW01557 Other views of refurbishment on RHW01558 to 01560 and 01562

View of SE corner of sitting room in the White House, home of Edward Sweetland photographer, High St, High Wycombe. about 1920
View of S.E. corner of sitting room in the White House home of Edward Sweetland photographer, showing furniture and piano.

From S. in the Music Library, Jaci Beaven and a library assistant, Queen Victoria Rd. High Wycombe. in the 1990s
Jaci Beaven, Music Librarian, and an assistant, possibly Carole Baker, in the Music Library High Wycombe.

Looking S, junctions with Chadwick St and Arnison Ave visible in a view S along Amersham Rd, Terriers, High Wycombe. Sept 1991
Amersham Rd from N. showing entrance to St Francis Church (left), junction with Arnison Ave, (left) newsagent number 95 (a.k.a. Archie's Stores) junction with Chadwick St (right), Royal Grammar School, housing on W. side

Two members of staff, Shirley Foster and Valerie Beadle, working in the Reference Library, Queen Victoria Rd. High Wycombe. about 1990
Two members of staff, Shirley Foster and Valerie Beadle, working in the Reference Library, High Wycombe.

Side view of a Davey-Paxman steam-driven engine (see also MHW01406). Glenister's chair factory, Bellfield Rd, High Wycombe. 1991
Side view of the Davey-Paxman steam-driven engine shown in MHW01406

From N, a view of S.E. section of S. room in Reference Library after refurbishment, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. 1990s
View of S.E. section of S. room in Reference Library after refurbishment with light grey metal shelving, tables and chairs in light wood, chairs with blue covers and tables with black tops. Map cabinets on right. Small display of photographs on back wall. Other views of refurbishment on RHW01557 to 01559 and RHW01561/2

View of NE corner of sitting room in the White House, home of Edward Sweetland photographer, High St, High Wycombe. about 1920
View of N.E. corner of sitting room in the White House, home of Edward Sweetland photographer, showing furniture and piano.

From S.E. in Lending Library, Mary Woodward at the checking-in desk, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. 1990s
Mary Woodward at the checking-in desk in the Lending Library with a member of the public.

From the Northwest, a view of demolition of shops between Red Cow Public house, seen on right, and premises of F.W.George in Frogmoor, High Wycombe. 1963
Demolition of shops between Red Cow Public house, seen on right, and F.W.George heating engineer and ironmonger in the Frogmoor, prior to the building of Tesco.

Seen from the East, a view of Martin Rickard (Reference Librarian) seated at enquiry desk in Reference Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. about 1990
Martin Rickard, Reference Librarian, seated at enquiry desk in Reference Library, shelving and card-index cabinet behind.

In Library foyer, group of Library staff dressed in military uniform for anniversary celebrations for V.E.Day, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. May 1995
Group of Library staff dressed in military uniform as part of anniversary celebrations for V.E. Day, standing in the foyer of High Wycombe Library in front of Union flag and display of posters from 1940s. Similar group on RHW01533

Looking S. across the valley, from junction with Priory Rd, a view down Amersham Hill, High Wycombe. about 1900
View of Amersham Hill from nr junction with Priory Rd across valley to lands of Wycombe Abbey, houses on W. side

Librarian Peter Mussett relaxing in the Library staff room, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. 1990s
Peter Mussett relaxing in the Library staff room. Copies of Hello and Vogue magazines on table.

From NE, a view of southern side of Oxford St, showing shops and the Rex Cinema. Oxford st, High Wycombe. Oct 1953
View of S. side of Oxford St. showing from E. Haven Restaurant, King's Head public house, Rex Cinema, Dring's {Ladies' and Gent's Tailors], Noel Bros. The Rex Cinema opened in Jan. 1938 and had white facings with a blue neon sign. Built on site of former cinema The Electroscope. It is showing The Desert Song in Technicolour. There are also two cars, a Currys van and pedestrians using the level crossing running N. to Frogmoor. Another view of Rex Cinema on RHW01518

An interior view showing dignitaries attending the stone laying ceremony at the new Hatters Lane school, Hatters Lane, High Wycombe. October 1939
Six dignitaries posed at the stone laying ceremony at the new Hatters Lane School. The Mayor, Councillor A.C. White introduced Alderman W.H. Tyzack who laid the stone. Alderman Owen Haines Chairman of the Education Committee, Alderman W.H.Healey and J.W.Moss, Borough Education Secretary, were also present.

From S.W. in Lending Library, a group photograph of the Library staff, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. March 1997
Group photograph of Library staff. From Left, back row Simon Lynn,[hide] * * * [/hide],|Gieler, Alison,|Mathers, Barbara,|Dickinson, Caroline,|Long, Janet,|Walton, Karen,|Andrews, Rob,|Rickard, Martin,|Hill, Sharon,|Woolley, Jocelyn,|Featherstone, Chris,|Smith, Janet,|Mussett, Peter,|Beaven, Jaci,|Jones, Sue,

From the West, demolition of interior of F.W.George heating engineer and ironmonger prior to building of Tesco. Frogmoor, High Wycombe. 1963
Demolition of interior of F.W.George heating engineer and ironmonger in Frogmoor prior to building of Tesco. Rear of building has sign 'Erected 1884', possibly former part of Salvation Army Citadel seen on left. Houses in Priory Rd and railway embankment in background

A group of primary school children from Castlefield School who took part in a concert, High Wycombe. December 1961
A group of some 46 primary school children from Castlefield School who took part in a concert.

seen from the east, a view of the Palace Cinema and adjoining Swimming Bath, Frogmoor, High Wycombe. about 1910
View of Palace Cinema and adjoining Swimming Bath with men and child outside, showing prices and times of films. Cinema converted from former Primitive Methodist chapel and Salvation Army Citadel. Opened Sept. 13th 1909, closed after fire 1912. The covered heated swimming baths were built by Aleck Stacey on the site of Wycombe Steam Saw Mills in 1910. Seen also on RHW01517

View of the NE corner of the Reference Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. 1992
View of N.E. corner of Reference Library to E. of entrance, showing shelving, photocopier and member of the public in Quick Reference section.

View from E of a house with prominent rounded architecture, near junction of Abbey Barn Lane and Kingsmead Rd, Wycombe Marsh, July 1990
View of house with round room, number 26 Kingsmead Rd, at junction of Abbey Barn La and Kingsmead Rd

From N. in Library foyer, children's art work to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the Library opening in Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. June 1992
View from stairs of the Library foyer with a display of children's art work including banners hanging from the stairwell to celebrate the sixtieth anniversary of the Library opening in Queen Victoria Rd. Other images of this display on RHW01586/7

In Library foyer, group of Library staff dressed in military uniform for anniversary celebrations for V.E.Day, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. May 1995
Group of Library staff dressed in military uniform as part of anniversary celebrations for V.E. Day, standing in the foyer of High Wycombe Library in front of Union flag and display of posters from 1940s. Similar group on RHW01534

Copy of a stereo photograph showing Queen Victoria, Prince Albert, Emperor Napoleon III and Empress Eugenie at the Crystal Palace, Sydenham. 1855
Copy of a stereo-pair taken at the Crystal Palace in 1855. Queen Victoria and Prince Albert are shown on a dais together with Emperor Napoleon III and Empress Eugenie. Behind them is classical sculpture of a young man and a horse. Two banners carry the initials V and N. Crowds look on, some standing on tiers above the arena.

Seen from SE, a view of front of the newly-completed Royal Grammar School, Amersham Rd, High Wycombe. April 1915
View of front of Royal Grammar School Amersham Rd with boarding house in background on left. Buildings designed by Arthur Vernon and opened in 1915. Showing emblem in portico and clock tower, also gate posts and fencing. Land in front purchased in 1923. Construction appears complete, pathways and rest of site being constructed/cleared. Character on Right may well be Arthur Vernon (HDC)

A view of Joan Fisher working in the office of the Library, Queen Victoria Rd. High Wycombe, about 1990
Joan Fisher working in the office of the Library, High Wycombe.

Interior view, showing six ladies preparing refreshments at a table laden with sandwiches and cakes at Frieth Bazaar, Frieth, nr Lane End. August 1964
Six Ladies at a table laden with sandwiches and cakes at Frieth Bazaar.

View looking NE from junction with Kingsmead Rd, along Abbey Barn Rd, Wycombe Marsh. July 1990
Abbey Barn Rd at junction with Kingsmead Rd, showing bridge over R. Wye, M.C. Bowden (scrap metal dealers) 94 Abbey Barn Rd

View from W. of Caribbean wedding party outside Salvation Army Citadel, Frogmoor, High Wycombe. about 1963
View of Caribbean wedding party outside Salvation Army Citadel in Frogmoor. Wall and tree fronting onto pavement.

From SW on first floor landing, displays celebrating 60th anniversary of opening of Library in Queen Victoria Rd. High Wycombe. June 1992
A display to celebrate the sixtieth anniversary of the opening of the Library in Queen Victoria Rd. On the left a display entitled High Wycombe Furniture Industry 1932 to 1992 with tools, some loaned from William Bartlett's factory and a poster from Ercol. On the right a display from Hague and Gill showing some of the work by Eric Gill then held in the Library. Painted banners by children hang from the bannisters, also part of the display. Bannisters subsequently removed and a wall built. Other images of this display on RHW01585/6

mentions.ne_span: High Wycombe Furniture Industry 1932 to 1992 with

text:
A group of primary school children posing for a photograph in the classroom of the old National School in White Hart St, High Wycombe. about 1913
A group of primary school children posing for a photograph in the classroom of the old National School in White Hart St. A board identifies them as Group 1. At the back of the room is a large cupboard and a blackboard and easel.

From NE, a view into the South room from the N room of Reference Library, after refurbishment. Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. 1990s.
View of S. room of Reference Library taken from N. room through arch after refurbishment with light grey metal shelving, tables and chairs in light wood, chairs with blue covers and tables with black tops. Painting on wall on right of N.room. Other views of refurbishment on RHW01557 and RHW01559 to 01562

Head and shoulder portrait of William Butler, founder and editor of the Bucks Free Press newspaper. location unknown. date unknown
Head and shoulder portrait of William Butler, founder and editor of the Bucks Free Press newspaper, which was founded in 1856.

From E. on landing, children's painted banners to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the opening of the Library in Queen Victoria Rd High Wycombe, June 1992
Painted banners, part of a display of children's art work to celebrate the sixtieth anniversary of the opening of the Library in Queen Victoria Rd. Taken before the bannisters on the landing were removed and a wall built. Other images of this display on RHW01585/7

Looking NE, a view of porch, bell-tower and S side of Holy Trinity Church, Prestwood. December 1989
Holy Trinity Church. View of porch and S side of the nave extension, bell-tower above. Church on left of A4128, S of village.

In Lending Library, staff dressed in 1930s style to celebrate 60th anniversary of the opening of High Wycombe Library in Queen Victoria Rd. 1992
Group of Library staff, in Lending Library, dressed in 1930s style to celebrate 60th anniversary of the opening of High Wycombe Library in Queen Victoria Rd. Table with celebration cake and champagne glasses. Same occasion on RHW01535

From the West (stage end) towards the front entrance doors, a view of the hall of the Royal Grammar School, Amersham Rd, High Wycombe. Sept 1938
Hall of Royal Grammar School, Amersham Rd. Viewed from stage end showing entrance doors to hall and beyond the front entrance to the school. Lower walls panelled, and globe lights.

Anniversary of V. E. Day in the Lending Library. Three members of staff dressed in military uniforms. Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. May 1995
Part of the celebrations for the anniversary of V. E. Day, three members of Library staff, Robert Andrews, Judith Shakespeare and Sharon Hill, dressed in military uniforms standing by a display in the Lending Library, with model dressed as airman.

S. towards door of Reference Library, a view after refurbishment, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe, in 1990s
View of N. room of Reference Library, photograph taken towards entrance. Showing Reference Library after refurbishment with light grey metal shelving, tables and chairs in light wood, chairs with blue covers and tables with black tops. Another view on RHW01561 Other views of refurbishment on RHW01558 to 01562

Ordnance map of Beaconsfield, Wooburn, Seer Green and Hedgerley showing sites of high explosives, January 1941
Ordnance map of Beaconsfield, Wooburn, Seer Green and Hedgerley showing sites of high explosives. Produced by Royal Air Corps.

Rough grassland and some modern housing adjacent to Dean Garden Rise (the houses pictured are at the bottom of the street), Deangarden Wood/Keep Hill area, High Wycombe. July 1990
Keep Hill area

Looking SE, a view of the S side of Oxford St from junction with Queens Sq to the Rex Cinema. Oxford St, High Wycombe. Sept 1950
View of S. side of Frogmoor from junction with Queen Sq. From E. Worlds Stores, Timpson, Bull Lane, Dolcis, Paige, Currys, Haven Restaurant, King's Head public house, Rex Cinema Ladies'and Gent's Tailors. Rex Cinema opened Jan. 1938, white facings to front with Rex sign, canopy with programme indicator. Showing 'All the Kings Men'.

From N.E. in Library foyer, Jill Eyers (geologist) with her Meet the Geologist exhibition, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. possibly 2001
Jill Eyers, geologist, standing in front of her exhibition entitled Meet the Geologist in the foyer of High Wycombe Library. The exhibition on Friday March 23rd from 11am to 5pm was part of Science Week. Members of the public are looking at rock samples. Posters on the wall behind include one for The Cygnets Saturday Shoppers Creche. Other images on RHW01582 and 01583

In the children's playground, a group of children posed on a rocking horse. Straight Bit, Flackwell Heath. March 1953
A group of children posed on a 'Ne Plus Ultra' Rocking Horse in the children's playground in Flackwell Heath. The horse was made by B. Hirst and Sons from Halifax, Yorkshire.

A group of boys performing a play called 'The Gardener' at Mill End School, Mill End Rd, High Wycombe. March 1952
A group of boys, three of whom are dressed as Roman soldiers, performing a play called 'The Gardener' at Mill End School.

Elevated view from All Saints church tower, showing demolition of buildings on corner of White Hart St and Paul's Row, High Wycombe. May 1948
Elevated view from tower of Parish Church of junction of High St, Church St, White Hart St and Paul's Row showing demolition of buildings in White Hart St and behind. On left Falcon Inn and Guildhall. Centre show Pauls Row with Swan Hotel and R.G. Stanners. In Church St. Lilley and Skinner, and Drings

View of the West and South sides of Bassetsbury Manor and bowling green, Bassetsbury Lane, High Wycombe. about 1960
W.and S.side of Bassetsbury Manor showing porch. Man playing bowls on green in foreground, seating and rose garden surrounding. Tennis courts to right. Building works to left in background, Spring Garden area.

Two members of a pantomime cast with a group of children, probably prize winners, in the Children's Library, Queen Victoria Rd. High Wycombe. about 1990
Members of the cast of a pantomime with a group of children, probably competition prize winners. Dressed as Dick Whittington and his cat, the actors are probably from the Swan Theatre, High Wycombe. The cat may be an actress. Another image on RHW01579

Looking West, a view of a horse and cart in the ford in Back Lane (Bassetsbury Lane/Kingsmead Road), Wycombe Marsh. 1920s?
Horse and cart crossing the ford, four cyclists and two children, a factory building and Woodbine Cottage

View from N of the Southernmost room of Reference Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. about 1990
View of S. room of Reference Library taken from doorway, showing table and chair and shelving which includes the Local Collection and Periodicals.

Viewed across foyer of the Library, a display to celebrate the anniversary of V. E. Day. Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. May 1995
Foyer of High Wycombe Library, a display to celebrate the anniversary of V. E. Day with flags and posters and a replica radio made by Martin Rickard. Another view of RHW01524

In Library foyer, Library staff dressed in 1930s style to celebrate 60th anniversary of the opening of High Wycombe Library in Queen Victoria Rd. 1992
Group of Library staff dressed in 1930s style to celebrate 60th anniversary of the opening of High Wycombe Library in Queen Victoria Rd. Same group o RHW01537, Same occasion on RHW01536

View from W. of machines clearing site prior to construction of Tesco supermarket in Frogmoor, High Wycombe. 1963
Machines clearing site prior to construction of Tesco supermarket in Frogmoor. Salvation Army Citadel on left to N. with sign outside. Houses in Priory Rd and Priory Ave, and railway embankment in background.

At Hughenden Vicarage, possibly at a garden party, a man supervises four teams of children at a game watched by a crowd. Hughenden. 1950's
At Hughenden Vicarage, possibly at a garden party, a man supervises four teams of children at a game on the skittles green watched by a crowd.

Looking NW, across Hamilton Rd, a view of the South and East sides of the Royal Grammar School and boarding house. Amersham Rd, High Wycombe. April 1915
View of South and East sides of Royal Grammar School Amersham Rd and boarding house in Hamilton Rd. Buildings designed by Arthur Vernon and opened in 1915.

From N.E. in Library foyer, Jill Eyers (geologist) with her Meet the Geologist exhibition, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. possibly 2001
Jill Eyers, geologist, talking to a member of the public in front of her exhibition entitled Meet the Geologist in the foyer of High Wycombe Library. The exhibition on Friday March 23rd from 11am to 5pm was part of Science Week. Another person is looking at rock samp Other images on RHW01581 and 01582

Celebrating the Coronation of Elizabeth II, a view of a street party in Park Street, High Wycombe. June 1953
View of a street party to celebrate the Coronation of Elizabeth II. Families, many wearing paper crowns, crowd around tables running along the street with children seated at them. A picture of the Queen hangs in a window.

Seen from the east, a view of the Electric Theatre and Skating Rink, Frogmoor, High Wycombe. about 1910
View of Electric Theatre and Skating Rink with man outside. White painted building with overhanging window on first floor and dome , decorated with strings of lights. Two double doors under arches. A.k.a. Swimming Baths opened in 1910, seen on RHW01516

Seen from West, a crane lifting a cement mixer onto site of construction of Tesco supermarket, Frogmoor, High Wycombe. 1963
Crane lifting cement mixer onto site of construction of Tesco supermarket in Frogmoor. Part of Red Cow public house on right and brick wall of previous building being supported.

Looking NW towards London Rd/Easton St, a view of a number of boys playing with model boats in the paddling pool, the Rye, High Wycombe. April 1963
Children sailing boats on paddling pool on Rye, against a background of Pann Mill (on left), and Trinity Congregational Church and shops with Coach and Horses public house (centre and right)

The children of Downley School gathered in the hall for speech day, School Close, Downley. July 1968
The children of Downley School gathered in the hall for speech day.

From N.E. in Library foyer, Jill Eyers (geologist) with her Meet the Geologist exhibition, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. possibly 2001
Jill Eyers, geologist, talking to a member of the public in front of her exhibition entitled Meet the Geologist in the foyer of High Wycombe Library. The exhibition on Friday March 23rd from 11am to 5pm was part of Science Week. Others are looking at rock samples. Other images on RHW01581 and 01583

View of S.W. corner of Reference Library showing shelving with books on Folklore and Science, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. about 1990
View of S.W. corner of Reference Library High Wycombe showing shelving with books on Folklore and Science.

View of reference display panel in Lending Library, relating to anniversary celebrations for V.E.day. Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. May 1995
Display panel with posters and notices of references facilities, part of anniversary celebrations for V.E.day in High Wycombe Library.

Ordnance map of Great Missenden, Great and Little Hampden and the Lee showing sites of high explosives and incendiary bombs, probably 1941
Ordnance map of Great Missenden, Great and Little Hampden and the Lee showing sites of high explosives and incendiary bombs. Produced by Royal Air Corps.

Interior of Lending Library showing tables and chairs set out for elderly persons party. Anniversary of V.E.Day, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. May 1995
Lending Library High Wycombe, staff member Heather Greenwood setting out tables and chairs for elderly persons party, part of anniversary celebrations for V.E.Day. Tables and Library decorated with flags. Librarian Peter Mussett and other staff members in background. Another view of RHW01531

Heraldic plaque relating to Sophia, the first wife of William who became 1st Marquis of Lansdowne, with motto 'Virtute Non Verbis', from Big School hall in Wycombe Abbey School, High Wycombe. date unknown
Heraldic plaque in a wooden frame with motto 'Virtute Non Verbis'. Hanging on a wooden background, the roof of the hall in the Big School, this is one of a series of 20 from Wycombe Abbey School. It relates to Sophia, (1st wife of William who became 1st Marquis of Lansdowne) who died in 1771.

From N.E. a postcard view of Tudor House, number 39, High St, High Wycombe. pre-1945
A postcard of Tudor House, number 39 High St, used by the National Provincial Bank. An early c18 facade of grey brick dressed in red, with a wide pedimented timber door-case. Overprinted with Christmas greetings.

Looking NW near the children's playground, a small crowd watch a man tending a model railway locomotive on The Rye, High Wycombe. April 1952
A small crowd watch a man wearing a trilby hat, Bob Dimmock, tending a model railway locomotive used to give children a ride along a raised track adjacent to the children's playground on the N. side of the Rye. Houses on the London Rd can be seen in the background.

Looking SW, a view showing cottages, later demolished, along the S side of Ford St, Wycombe Marsh. 1958
View of cottages on S side of Ford St, later demolished in last quarter of 1960.

Looking N/NE, possibly a garden party where onlookers watch a man, woman and child playing a game on the lawn of the Vicarage, Hughenden. 1950's
At Hughenden Vicarage, possibly a garden party, a man, woman and child, probably a family group, playing a skittle-like game. Others look on

Looking E, a view of the actress Diana Dors receiving flowers as she arrived to open the Donner superstore in Frogmoor, High Wycombe. May 1956
The actress Diana Dors receiving flowers as she arrived to open the Donner superstore in Frogmoor. Same event on BFP01771

Looking SE from just below the vicarage, a view of three girls and two boys at a kissing gate in Hughenden Park, Hughenden. 1950's
In Hughenden Park, just below the vicarage, three girls and two boys at a kissing gate in a metal fence.

Looking SE, a view of children giving a display of maypole dancing on the lawns of Hughenden Vicarage, possibly at a garden party. Hughenden. 1950's
Children give a display of maypole dancing on the lawns at Hughenden Vicarage. Dart board in background. Possibly at a garden party.

Looking N, a view along A4128 from its junction with Hatches Lane, Great Kingshill. February 1990
View along A4128 from its junction with Hatches Lane on left and cricket field on right. Road to Spurlands End with car park adjoining on right.

Looking N from W side of A4128, a view of the S side of Holy Trinity Church with war memorial and hall, Prestwood. December 1989
View of the South side of Holy Trinity Church, Wycombe Rd. War Memorial to East and building, possibly church hall, seen in background.

View of Lending Library. Staff member Kari Dorme dressed in W.R.A.F. uniform for anniversary of V.E.Day. Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. May 1995
Member of Library staff, Kari Dorme, dressed in W.R.A.F. uniform standing next to model dressed as airman, part of anniversary of V.E.Day celebrations in High Wycombe Library.

Ordnance map of Ivinghoe, Cheddington, Marsworth, Pitstone and Edlesborough showing sites of high explosives, January 1941
Ordnance map of Ivinghoe, Cheddington, Marsworth, Pitstone and Edlesborough showing sites of high explosives. Produced by Royal Air Corps.

Seen from SW, elderly people enjoying a party as part of anniversary of V.E. Day celebrations in Lending Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. May 1995
Elderly people enjoying a party held as part of anniversary of V.E. Day celebrations in Lending Library High Wycombe. Tables with food, flags decorating the walls,enlarged photograph of chair arch on wall, Post Office building seen through window.

Looking N, a view of a crowd awaiting the arrival of Diana Dors to open the Donner superstore, Frogmoor, High Wycombe. May 1956
A crowd gathered in Frogmoor, controlled by two policemen, await the arrival of the actress Diana Dors who was to open a new superstore owned by Harry Donner. On the W. side is number 31A and Donner's Superstore annexe and an electrical shop. In the background the Intimate Theatre. The woman on the far left, wearing a pale overcoat and holding a 'bucket' handbag and a Brownie camera, is Carol Aldridge.

The same event is shown in BFP01772

looking N from the junction with Oxford St, the scene after a freak snowstorm. Frogmoor, High Wycombe. April 1908
View of Frogmoor after freak snowstorm on April 26th 1908. In the foreground a horse trough stands in front of a road sign. The fountain is in the centre and the Technical School in the background.

Looking NW, a view of the Mayor and Corporation in procession to the Town Hall for the visit of the Queen. Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. April 1962
A procession of dignitaries including the Mayor, Councillor Hann, passing the library en route to the Town Hall for the visit of the Queen.

View of party in Lending Library for elderly persons to celebrate the anniversary of V.E. Day, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. May 1995
Party for elderly persons to celebrate the anniversary of V.E. Day held in High Wycombe Lending Library. Library staff including the Librarian, Peter Mussett, helping out. Tables and walls decorated with flags. Follows RHW01529 and RHW01531

View from W. of crane lifting sheet-piling in an early stage of construction of Tesco supermarket, Frogmoor, High Wycombe. 1963
Two men watching crane lifting piling/part of steel frame in early stage of construction of Tesco supermarket in Frogmoor. Houses in Priory Rd. and Priory Ave. and railway embankment in background.

Looking N/NE, a view showing cottage and barn, later demolished, on N side of Ford St, Wycombe Marsh, 1958
View of N side of Ford St showing cottage with adjacent timber barn. Later demolished in quarter ending Sept. 60

Colin Dexter standing with Kari Dorme and Peter Mussett in the Lending Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. about 1990
Colin Dexter standing with Kari Dorme and Peter Mussett at one of his public talks in High Wycombe Lending Library . Colin Dexter is wearing a Remembrance poppy. Kari Dorme is holding a copy of The Silent World of Nicholas Gunn by Colin Dexter.

mentions.ne_span: The Silent World of Nicholas Gunn

text:
Looking W, a view of Hughenden Church showing E face and tower beyond. Grave of Benjamin Disraeli seen to the right. Hughenden. c 1909
View of Hughenden Church showing the East face and tower beyond. Grave of Benjamin Disraeli seen to right of tree.

Ordnance map of Wendover, Weston Turville, Halton, Gt and Little Kimble, Stoke Mandeville, and Ellesborough showing sites of high explosives, Jan. 1941
Ordnance map of Wendover, Weston Turville, Halton, Great and Little Kimble, Stoke Mandeville, Hartwell and Ellesborough. showing sites of high explosives. Produced by Royal Air Corps. MHW01739 same map showing incendiary bombs.

View from S. of the North room of the Reference Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. about 1990
View of N. room of Reference Library showing shelving on E. side including Community Information, map cabinet and telephone directories. Also five study tables and chairs.

A group of primary school children at the crowning of the Queen of the May at the Church of England School, Loakes Rd, High Wycombe. about 1930
A group of primary school children at the crowning of the Queen of the May at the Church of England School, Loakes Rd

Aerial view of Hughenden Rd, Hughenden Manor, Amersham Rd, Terriers, West Wycombe Rd, June 1989
Aerial view of Hughenden Rd, Hughenden Manor, Amersham Rd, Terriers, West Wycombe Rd. NE corner (top left) showing Widmer End, SE showing Hatters Lane at junction with Totteridge Lane, SW showing West Wycombe Rd after junction with Desborough Ave, NW showing woods and fields of Downley.

Looking S from near the junction with Hatches Lane, a view showing houses on either side of Warrendene Rd, Hughenden. March 1992
View along Warrendene Rd. from junction with Hatches La. showing houses on either side.

Pauline Champion helping herself to food at her leaving party in the staff room of the Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. 1992
Pauline Champion helping herself to food at her leaving party in the staff room of the Library, High Wycombe. Another image on RHW01576

A colour postcard view of girls working in their gardens in Wycombe Abbey School, High Wycombe. about 1910.
Girls working on their gardens in Wycombe Abbey School.

Looking SE, a view of two single storey brick and flint cottages standing on left of road at Lower North Dean, nr Naphill. July 1989
Two single storey brick and flint cottages standing on left of road. One has an outside door into attic area

View from S.W. of flatbed lorry with crane used in the construction of the Tesco supermarket, Frogmoor, High Wycombe. late 1963
Flatbed lorry arriving or departing with crane (identified by 'Elstree') used in the construction of the Tesco supermarket. Passing Welling and Routledge Surveyors and Estate Agents number 46-48 Frogmoor. Building to N. being demolished.

mentions.ne_span: Welling and Routledge Surveyors and Estate Agents

text:
Harold Macmillan opening the 1000th house built by Wycombe Rural District Council. Berryfields estate, Princes Risborough. January 1952
Harold Macmillan, Minister for Housing and Local Government, opened the 1000th house built by Wycombe Rural District Council after the war on the Berryfield estate in Princes Risborough. The occupiers were Mr. and Mrs. Benjamin Legg. Councillor West also attended.

Interior of Lending Library, tables and chairs laid out for elderly persons party. Anniversary of V.E.Day. Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. May 1995
Lending library High Wycombe with tables, chairs and food set out for elderly persons' party, part of anniversary celebrations for V.E. Day.Walls and tables decorated with flags, display panel with posters. Staff in background. Another view of RHW01529

Members of a pantomime cast presenting tickets to a girl probably as a competition prize, Children's Library, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. about 1990
Members of the cast of a pantomime presenting tickets to a girl probably as a competition prize. Dressed as Dick Whittington and his cat, the actors are probably from the Swan Theatre, High Wycombe. The cat may be an actress. Another girl sits in the foreground. Another image on RHW01580

Looking SE, to junction with Kings Sq, a view of cottages and old Congregational Church later demolished. Ford St, Wycombe Marsh. 1958
View of cottages at junction of Ford St and Kings Sq. Wycombe Marsh. Numbers 2,4 and 6 Ford St on left and 1 and 3 Kings Sq on right. The old Congregational Chapel is in the centre.The cottages in Ford St were demolished in the last quarter of 1960.

At Hughenden Vicarage, possibly at a garden party, children taking part in team games sit on the lawn watched by a crowd. Hughenden. 1950's
At Hughenden Vicarage, possibly at a garden party, children taking part in team games sit on the lawn watched by a crowd. Skittle enclosure in background.

View of a display of nine chairs of different designs. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1995
A display of nine chairs of different designs in Wycombe Museum. A small display case at the left holds small examples of chairs.

Looking SE, a view with scaffolding surrounding the site of demolition of the Dovecot at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990
Scaffolding around the site of the demolition of the Dovecot damaged in winter storms in 1988. Behind stands Wycombe Museum, formerly Castle Hill House.

Looking West, a scene of Wycombe Wanderers football team warming up on their training ground, Loakes Rd, High Wycombe. August 1957
Wycombe Wanderers football team warming up with a 'piggy-back' race on their training ground before their next game in the Isthmian League. Loakes House seen in background.

Looking NW from just before junction with Church Lane, a view of an early cyclist and the N side of the High St, West Wycombe. c 1900
View along N side of High St. showing on right timber framed Church Loft with shops below and archway to Church La. and ancient clock. C16 and C17 buildings, some with C18 and C19 frontages. A man on a tricycle passes by some piles of chairs.

An exhibition of pictures in an upper gallery of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. date unknown
Exhibition in upper galleries [md] Room with a fireplace.

Two young boys carrying their fishing gear, walking along the bank of the River Thames near Henley. 1960s?
Two young boys walking along the bank of the River Thames carrying their fishing gear. A man stands outside a pair of cottages on the opposite bank.

In a tent in the grounds of Wycombe Museum, party food at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Party food set out in a tent at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum.

Two women, one called Jackie Blake, being presented to HRH Prince Philip. location unknown. 1960s?
Two women, one called Jackie Blake, being presented to HRH Prince Philip.

Looking N, a view of members watching Scottish dancing at the 25th anniversary party of High Wycombe Society. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Members of the High Wycombe Society including Diana Lawson and Sheila Fooks, watching Scottish dancing at the 25th anniversary party of Society. Wycombe Museum, formerly Castle Hill House, seen in background. The Caledonian Society provided dancers. Refreshment tent on left. Centre a model of a reclining boy on the grass.

A view of part of an old kitchen range, standing in an area tiled with large glazed brown tiles. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990
Part of an old kitchen range, standing in an area tiled with large glazed brown tiles. Another wider view on MHW02457

A group of some 48 men (and one woman?) possibly a committee, posed outside the front of the Vicarage at Stokenchurch. c 1900
A group of some 48 men (and one woman?) possibly a committee, posed outside the front of the Vicarage at Stokenchurch.

Group of chairmakers (including 'Grampy Styles') posed in the yard of Howland's furniture factory. Desborough Rd, c.1900?
Group of chairmakers (8 men and a boy) posed in the yard of Howland's furniture factory with two decorated chairs. One is Grampy Styles, possibly the father of Eva Styles who married Len Towersey.

View at the party to mark 25 years of the High Wycombe Society; members country dancing in the grounds of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
At the celebration to mark 25 years of the High Wycombe Society, members take part in country dancing, some in highland dress, in the grounds of Wycombe Museum where a party was held. Same event seen on MHW02211 and 02212

View of a line of men working at lathes etc. in the machine shop of Broom and Wade, Hughenden Ave, High Wycombe. c 1936
Line of men working in the machine shop in Broom and Wade. Machinery driven by flat overhead belts

From W. to E. side of New Rd, view of 95 New Rd, the home of Gladys Towersey and William Hurst. Booker, High Wycombe. about 1935
View of 95 New Rd Booker, the home of Gladys Kathleen Towersey and William Mathias Hurst.

View of youngsters playing in the River Wye at Loudwater, September 1956
Six youngsters playing in the River Wye at Loudwater watched by six others on the bank, two with bicycles.

Inside the Guildhall, display panels forming part of the Summer Exhibition 'Our House'. Guildhall, High St, High Wycombe. 1992
In the Guildhall,display boards with photographs and information panels as part of the Guildhall Summer Exhibition 'Our House'. At the far end the dais with the coat of arms above.

Looking NE in the grounds of Castle Hill House, Mary Towersey posed in the garden. Priory Ave, High Wycombe. March 1938
Mary Towersey in a maids uniform posed by a rockery in the garden of Castle Hill House

A formal photograph taken at the Annual Dinner of the High Wycombe Professional and Business Women's Association. location unknown. Dec 1962
A formal photograph taken at the Annual Dinner of the High Wycombe Professional and Business Women's Association.

mentions.ne_span: High Wycombe Professional and Business Women's Association
High Wycombe Professional and Business Women's Association

text:
Group of young men, some in cricket clothes, posed with a board reading Gents C.C. location unknown. c 1910
Group of young men, some in cricket clothes, posed with a board reading Gents C.C.

View of a reconstruction of a 1950's dining room, part of a display called 'Continuity and Change' at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe, 1995
In Wycombe Museum, a mock-up of a 1950's dining room as part of a display called Continuity and Change. Three chairs of different designs are seen around a wooden table with drop down flaps.On the table a cup and saucer, sugar bowl and radio of the period. To the left a bookcase with a clock. Right a gilt framed mirror. Information panels include After the War, The Utility Scheme and Ercol and G-Plan Furniture. Also seen on MHW02454

Looking N, a view of children playing in front of (mainly) C18 cottages in Church Lane, West Wycombe. 1911
View of children in Church Lane. A high wall on E side shows the former vicarage. On W side, houses; the one with outside steps is dated 1722.

Looking NW, a view of terraced houses, West End Hall and St John's Church, on the N side of West End Rd, High Wycombe. Feb 2001
Terraced houses on N. side of West End Rd, West End Hall and St John's Church.

Looking NW from opposite entrance to Church Lane, a view of Church Loft and surrounding buildings on N side of High St, West Wycombe. c 1900
View of Church Loft with clock on W end and weather vane on roof. Ground floor has chairs stacked outside and man in work apron. To E, a shop with blind over window and advertisement for Hudson's and Venus soap. To W, entrance to Church Lane and cottages.

Members at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society in the gardens of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Members of the High Wycombe Society watching speeches or an entertainment at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum.

Inside the Guildhall, display panels forming part of the Summer Exhibition 'Our House'. Guildhall, High St, High Wycombe. 1992
Display boards with titles including Clearance, Sanitation, Slums, Victorian Washday and Tudor Wycombe, all part of the Guildhall Summer Exhibition 'Our House' . Mainly photographs and information panels, there are some objects in a wooden display case. Windows on the left overlook the High St.

Looking East along the front of Castle Hill House, Mary Towersey in a maids uniform posed by a sundial. Priory Ave, High Wycombe. March 1938
Mary Towersey in a maids uniform posed by a sundial in the garden of Castle Hill House

Inside the Guildhall, part of the Summer Exhibition 'Our House' showing household items from the 18c. Guildhall, High St, High Wycombe. 1992
Part of the Guildhall Summer Exhibition 'Our House' showing two chairs, a desk, a vase and books from the 18c on the dais at the N. end of the Guildhall.

View of a new display of caning and rush work, after remodelling of the exhibition area in Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
A new display after remodelling of exhibition area of Wycombe Museum showing caning and rush seating techniques. Samples of cane and rush work hang on the wall. A cane seated chair is shown. Also seen on MHW02448 and 02449

probably a door-knocker, a decorative carving of face with leaves and a band in the hair, with leaves and berries to the side. location unknown. date unknown
probably a door-knocker, a decorative carving of face with leaves and a band in the hair. More leaves and berries hang down on either side of the face and meet underneath with an oval medallion.

Parker-Knoll Cricket Club posed outside a cricket pavilion after winning Div.I and Div.II Furniture Trades League. location unknown. 1949
Parker-Knoll Cricket Club posed outside a cricket pavilion after winning Div.I and Div.II, Furniture Trades League

Inside the Guildhall, part of the Summer Exhibition 'Our House' showing a sitting room typical of the 1960s. Guildhall, High St, High Wycombe. 1992
Part of the Guildhall Summer Exhibition 'Our House'. The display shows a sitting room in the early 1960s with a television, sideboard, radio, settee, pouffe, standard lamp and ornaments.

Looking SE from an upper window, members of the Caledonian Soc at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Seen from an upper window in Wycombe Museum, members of the Caledonian Society, invited to lead the Scottish dancing at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum. Barbara Rippington, Programme Sec. of the Society and a dancer seen with leather jacket.

Photograph of a chain and attached frame, which contains the photograph of a man. location unknown. 1890's?
Photograph of a chain and attached frame, which contains the photograph of a man. A ruler on the left side shows the frame to be 3.5cms high.

Young men posed in front of a coach on an outing from the 'Swan' pub. Rupert Busby, known as Jack, 4th from right. location unknown. 1930's?
Young men posed in front of a coach on an outing from the 'Swan' pub. Rupert Busby, known as Jack, 4th from right.

Portrait of Paul Stevenson in his studio, before a painting of a chair from the Museum. location unknown. 1990
Paul Stevenson in his studio with a painting of a Museum chair.[md]

A metal measure inscribed Wickham 1672 Imperial Standard 1826 Bushel, in Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave. High Wycombe, date unknown
A circular metal container with two side handles inscribed Wickham 1672 Imperial Standard 1826 Bushel

Tommy Tranter standing next to his green-grocer's cart with a young Ted Busby, High Wycombe. 1910 -20s.
Tommy Tranter standing next to his painted green grocer's cart laden with fruit including hands of bananas. Next to the horse stands a young Ted Busby.

Louise Perrin with Victoria Wood at her farewell party in the Education Room of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1999
Louise Perrin Documentation Assistant at Wycombe Museum at her farewell party with Victoria Wood the Curator. Both are holding framed photographs which were presented to Louise. Same event seen on MHW 02207 to 02209

Looking SW from N side of road nr St.John's Church, a view of a car park, formerly terraced houses in West End Rd, High Wycombe. Feb 2001
View of land in West End Rd, then in use as a car park, formerly the site of terraced houses including no.55. Back of houses on N. side of Wendover St. seen in background.

Inside the Guildhall, display boards set up in readiness for the Summer Exhibition 'Our House'. High St, High Wycombe. 1992
Display boards set up in readiness for the Summer Exhibition 'Our House' inside the Guildhall

View of part of a display of early kitchen furniture and equipment in Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
A display of early kitchen furniture and equipment in Wycombe Museum including a range and a Windsor chair. This display is post-refurbishment. [md]

Photograph of a painting 'Prototype Duo', by Paul Stevenson. location unknown. painted in 1990
Photograph of a painting by Paul Stevenson called Prototype Duo painted in oil, pencil and gesso in 1990. Reproduced in the Star newspaper.

Naphill United F.C. with Rupert Busby (known as Jack) pose after winning Div.1 Risborough and District League 1932 - 33. location unknown. c 1933
Team of Naphill United F.C. pose after winning Div.1 Risborough and District League 1932 - 33, having previously won 1929-30. Rupert Busby, known as Jack, far left, middle row.

Two young women stand in front of a display, part of a larger exhibition, possibly in the Guildhall, High St, High Wycombe. 1990's?
Two young women stand in front of a display, part of a larger exhibition, possibly in the Guildhall at W. end of High St. The display includes model animals and clothing.

View of a cabinet maker's tool chest together with information panels; part of a display at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1995
A cabinet maker's tool chest together with information panels in a display in Wycombe Museum. Four examples of chair styles hang on the wall behind.

Five members of staff, including Marc Meltonville, in an office at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
Five members of staff in an office in Wycombe Museum. Foreground Marc Meltonville, standing back right John.

Looking NE, a view of the Red Lion being lifted through an upper window at the front of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1995
Originally catalogued as raising an exhibit for the Dinosaur Exhibition in 1994, re-catalogued by James Rattue as the Red Lion been raised through an upper window from the ground floor in 1995.[md] The Red Lion stood on the portico of the hotel of the same name in the High St. being replaced in 1956. Also seen on MHW02410 and MHW02238

In a marquee in gardens of Wycombe Museum, the bar at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Peter Hazzard left, one of the barmen, serves guests at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum. There was a display by High Wycombe Caledonian Society.

Looking S, a view of a group gathered for the opening of the tennis courts at High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital, Barracks Rd, High Wycombe. Aug 1924
Group of men and women, including some nurses, in front of the main entrance to High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital for the opening of the tennis courts.

mentions.ne_span: High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital
High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital

text:
An elderly couple, Mr and Mrs Bill Hatt, cut a Golden Wedding Anniversary(?) cake at a celebration in the village hall, North Dean, Naphill. about 1977
A celebration cake being cut by an elderly couple. The room suggests a village hall with wooden walls and a notice board. Next to the cake are presents with gold ribbon suggesting a Golden Wedding Anniversary.
The gentleman pictured is Mr William (Bill) Hatt who was born in North Dean in 1901. The lady is his wife Ethel Lilian Hatt (nee Atkins) who was born in the area in 1911, and died in 1992. 
Mr Hatt, who died in North Dean in 1986, used to drive a lorry which was used for general haulage around the area. The Hatt family were in North Dean for many years.

Looking E from above Suffield Road, an aerial view of Marlow Hill A404, Queen Alexandra Rd and Abbey Way roundabout, High Wycombe. c 1990
Aerial view of High Wycombe with Marlow Hill A404 running from N and Queen Alexandra Rd from W towards Abbey Way. Wycombe General Hospital centre and W of Marlow Hill, Wycombe College to N and Wycombe Abbey School E of Marlow Hill. Bottom left Gas Works and Rutland St. Top left the Lake in Wycombe Abbey grounds. Top right Wycombe Abbey grounds. Bottom right Tom Burt's Hill.

Looking W in front of Wycombe Museum, a view of Ronald Swains reading at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society, Priory Ave, High Wycombe, June 1993
Ronald Swains reading at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum. Other guest include Ann Simone behind bench on left.

View of part of a Ward with a nurse seated at a desk in the newly-opened High Wycombe General Hospital, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. 1966
View of part of a ward of the newly opened High Wycombe General Hospital, with nurse seated at desk.

Group of eighteen nurses from High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital probably in the hospital grounds, Barracks Rd, High Wycombe. July 1924
Group of eighteen nurses from High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital posed in probably the hospital grounds in Barracks Rd. The hospital was opened in 1923 and demolished in 1971.

mentions.ne_span: High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital
High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital

text:
Looking NW from above the Abbey Grounds, an aerial view of lower Marlow Hill and central High Wycombe. c 1990
View of central High Wycombe with Marlow Hill A404 from bottom left, top left junction of Desborough Rd and Short St., top right Priory Rd, bottom right grounds of Wycombe Abbey School. W. of Marlow Hill Wycombe General Hospital. N. of hospital Wycombe College. On far right, Wycombe Swan Theatre with the Fire Station in front. Parish Church with green roof on right with Little Market House in front.

In a marquee in gardens of Wycombe Museum, the bar at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Peter Hazzard left, one of the barmen, serves guests at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum.

Looking SW from above Abbey Way roundabout, an aerial view of High Wycombe General Hospital and surroundings, High Wycombe. mid 1990s
Aerial view of High Wycombe General Hospital with junction of Marlow Hill A404 and Queen Alexandra Rd. On bottom left buildings of Wycombe Abbey School, top left N.car park of hospital, top right another hospital car park, bottom right Wycombe College. To W. building site on former Wycombe Wanderers Football Grounds Loakes Park.

Inside the Guildhall, part of the Summer Exhibition 'Our House', showing a display entitled Victorian Washday. High St, High Wycombe. 1992
Part of the Guildhall Summer Exhibition 'Our House', a display entitled Victorian Washday with household items. On right the dais at N. end of the room.

An exhibition of some twenty-two wooden chairs of various designs, at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990
An exhibition of some twenty-two wooden chairs including Windsor chairs of various designs, a bentwood chair and a Lloyd Loom chair.

Louise Perrin receiving a framed photograph at her farewell party in the Education Room of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1999
Louise Perrin, Documentation Assistant at Wycombe Museum with Victoria Wood Museum Curator, being presented with a framed photograph at her farewell party held in the Education Room at the Museum. From left to right, Keith Wilkins (just seen), Leslie Dandy, Mary Dandy, Louise Perrin and Victoria Wood. Same event seen on MHW02207 to 02210

Looking E/NE from above Kingsley Crescent, an aerial view of Marlow Hill A404, Abbey Way, Queen Alexandra Rd and Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. c 1990
Aerial view of High Wycombe with Marlow Hill A404 running from N towards Abbey Way. Wycombe General Hospital centre and W of Marlow Hill, to N Wycombe College and the Swan Theatre, to E Wycombe Abbey School. The Abbey Lake seen centre top. Bottom left Tom Burt's Hill and C. of E. Combined School. Top left junction of Queen Victoria Rd High St. Crendon St. and Eaton St. Top right grounds of Wycombe Abbey School. Bottom right Tom Burts Hill and Kingsley Crescent.

Inside the Guildhall, display boards forming part of the Summer Exhibition 'Our House'. Guildhall, High St, High Wycombe. 1992
