Display boards, part of the Guildhall Summer Exhibition 'Our House', including topics Medieval Wycombe and Tudor Wycombe. In addition to the photograph and information panels there are two wooden display cases. The door on the right leads to the kitchen and the Shelbourne room.

Part of an exhibition of old household utensils displayed in the kitchen at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1995
An exhibition of old household utensils displayed in the kitchen at Wycombe Museum including a chair, plates, bottles and pans. This display also on MHW02203

Looking W from above the Abbey Grounds, an aerial view of lower Marlow Hill and part of southwestern area of High Wycombe. c 1990
Aerial view of High Wycombe General Hospital with Marlow Hill A404 from left to right. Bottom left and right grounds of Wycombe Abbey School, top left Tom Burt's Hill, top right junction of Temple St. and Desborough Rd. On left N. side of Queen Alexandra Rd. Wycombe College. New flats being constructed W. of Hospital on former grounds of Wycombe Wanderers Football Club Loakes Park.

Louise Perrin receiving a framed photograph at her farewell party in the Education Room of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1999
Louise Perrin, Documentation Assistant at Wycombe Museum, being presented with a framed photograph at her farewell party held in the Education Room at the Museum. From left to right, John Rutland, Keith Wilkins, Richard Bird, Leslie Dandy, Mary Dandy, Louise Perrin and Victoria Wood. Same event seen on MHW02207 to 02210

Looking S from College Grounds, a view of front of the main block of the General Hospital during Phase 1. High Wycombe. October 1986
View of front of the main block of High Wycombe General Hospital during Phase 1 taken from Queen Alexandra Rd.

In a marquee, M. Simmons and I. Stone at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave. High Wycombe . June 1993
Margaret Simmons and Ian Stone left and possibly Owen Rush, guests at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum.

In the Guildhall, a display from the Summer Exhibition 'Our House'. High St, High Wycombe. 1992
A display from the Guildhall Summer Exhibition 'Our House', with a carved chair, chest, and panels and a ewer. On the chest is carved Fere God I Love God. On the walls are photographs and information posters. Other views of Our House Exhibition on MHW02237 and 35382

The Gores with R Williams at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society in gardens of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Centre John and Joan Gore talking to Reginald Williams in the refreshment tent at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum. Other members seen left and right.

Looking NW, an interior view of entrance foyer of High Wycombe General Hospital, Queen Alexandra Rd, High Wycombe. probably 1966
View of entrance foyer of High Wycombe General Hospital taken from balcony with entrance doors at top. Desk to left and seat on right.

Looking E, a view of guests at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society, Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Betty Barrett and other guests at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum.

Eight children from Hamilton Rd School listen to a talk at an exhibition of chairs in Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. early 1990's?
A group of eight children from Hamilton Rd School listening to a talk in an exhibition room in Wycombe Museum. Around them stands a display of eleven labelled wooden chairs. On the wall hang posters and two pictures, one of a man and one of a woman.

Owen Dean by his workshop, shaping a rough billet with a draw shave in Hampden Woods, Great Hampden. December 1949
Owen Dean sitting in front of his workshop in Hampden Woods shaping a rough billet with a draw shave. To the left a pile of chair legs or stretchers. By the shed a grinding wheel. The external part of the pole lathe is seen leading into the shed.

View of the interior of chapel, part of the Phase 1B building of High Wycombe General Hospital, Queen Alexandra Rd, High Wycombe. probably 1966?
View of interior of chapel, part of the Phase 1B building of High Wycombe General Hospital. The chapel and lecture room were situated on the top floor of the main block.

Olive Scruton at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society in the gardens of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Olive Scruton right talking to another woman at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum. A tent for refreshments left, and other members right.

Looking W, a view of the model of new hospital buildings off Marlow Hill, High Wycombe. early 1960's
Model of new hospital building and car park seen from Marlow Hill. Queen Alexandra Rd. leading W. from bottom right.

In the gardens of Wycombe Museum, B. and C. Wallis at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society. Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Barbara and Christopher Wallis with others at a display by High Wycombe Caledonian Society at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum.

Looking N, a view of the Cottage Hospital with figures on the veranda. Priory Rd, High Wycombe. late 1880's?
Exterior of High Wycombe Cottage Hospital and gardens with two nurses and two men on the veranda.

Looking W, a view across the lawns towards the vicarage of All Saints Parish Church. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
View across gardens in front of Wycombe Museum towards the vicarage of All Saints Parish Church in Priory Ave. House on W. side of Priory Ave. seen behind.

Owen Dean splitting a billet with a beetle and wedge outside his workshop in Hampden Woods, Great Hampden. about 1949
Owen Dean working in Hampden Woods in front of his workshop, splitting the billet with a 'beetle and wedge'. He is surrounded by wood cut at various stages.

Members dancing at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society in the gardens of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Barbara Wallis in floral skirt, one of the members of High Wycombe Society joining in Scottish dancing at the 25th anniversary party of Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum. Refreshment tent seen in background.

Looking SE, a view of the back of High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital, Barracks Rd, High Wycombe. late 1920's?
View of back of High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital, Barracks Rd. opened 1923 demolished 1971. On the left buildings of Wycombe Abbey School on the E side of Marlow Hill.

In a marquee, M. Simmons and I. Stone at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave. High Wycombe . June 1993
Margaret Simmons and Ian Stone, guests at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum.

Looking S from car park, a view of the NW corner of the main building of the General Hospital during Phase 1, Queen Alexandra Rd. High Wycombe. October 1986
View of north-west of the main building of High Wycombe General Hospital taken from the car park during Phase 1. Canopy on W. side shows entrance to Accident and Emergency. Sign to indicate different departments.

Looking W across the gardens, a Craft Fair housed in tents in the grounds next to Castle Mound. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. Spring 1991?
A Craft Fair housed in tents in the grounds of Wycombe Museum. [md] Right a mound, sometimes named Castle Mound, was the site of the motte and bailey castle in the 12C.A marked path leads to the top. Behind houses in Priory Ave. A woman walks in the grounds. Flowers suggest Spring.

View of a display on caning and rushing techniques with examples and two chairs. In a gallery in Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1995
A display on caning and rushing techniques in Wycombe Museum including examples of seat panels, a photograph of men at work, tools, two chairs and information panels.

Looking NE towards junction of A40/Marlow Hill, a view of the War Memorial Hospital and the General Hospital, Barracks Rd, High Wycombe. c 1970
Wycombe War Memorial Hospital in foreground with Wycombe General in background. Behind the General Hospital is the Fire Station, The Liberal Club and in Queen Victoria Rd. the Police Station and the District Council Offices. To the right the buildings of Wycombe Abbey School.

Ron Sims and partner at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society, in the gardens of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Ronald Sims, Minutes Secretary of the High Wycombe Society with partner dancing at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum.

Looking N, a view of the Red Lion being lifted through an upper window at the front of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1995
The Red Lion, formerly standing on the portico of the hotel of the same name in the High St, being raised from the ground floor through an upper window. It was replaced on the portico in 1956 and moved initially to Hughenden Manor. Also seen on MHW02409 and MHW02238

looking S from car park, a view of front of the main block of the General Hospital during Phase 1. High Wycombe. October 1986
Close up view of front of the main building of High Wycombe General Hospital taken from the car park during Phase 1.

Looking SW along Barracks Rd, a view of the accommodation blocks for the General Hospital, High Wycombe. c 1970
View along Barracks Rd showing accommodation blocks for Wycombe General Hospital, which were completed in 1964.

Looking N, a view of men building a flint and brick wall as part of the refurbishment of buildings to the rear of the Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990
Men building a flint and brick wall, part of the refurbishment of buildings to the rear of Wycombe Museum. In the background are houses in The Haystacks.

Looking SW from junction of Marlow Hill/Queen Alexandra Rd, a model view of the new hospital building, off Marlow Hill, High Wycombe. early 1960's
Model of new hospital building and car park with nurses' accommodation in background. Marlow Hill on bottom left, Queen Alexandra Rd. bottom right

Looking NE, a view of the buildings of High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital, Barracks Rd, High Wycombe. late 1920's/early 1930's?
View of main entrance and adjoining buildings of High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital opened in 1923 and demolished 1971.

mentions.ne_span: High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital

text:
Looking N, a view of the celebration cake at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
A decorated cake with a flower arrangement on a table with decorative cloth at the front entrance of Wycombe Museum. This was the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society. In the porch electrical connections for the microphones and an electronic keyboard.

Guests at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society, Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Guests enjoying supper at a party to celebrate the 25th anniversary of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum. Roger Lawson, Chairman of the Society, standing.

A view two caned chairs in part of a new display, after remodelling of the exhibition area in Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
A new display of chairs after remodelling of exhibition area of Wycombe Museum. Both chairs seen are cane seated. The smaller one is a traveller's sample of a cane folding chair. There is a poster for J. Elliott and Son of Desborough Rd and Shaftesbury St High Wycombe. Another angle of MHW02445 and 02446

Looking NE, High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital in front with Phase 1 of the General Hospital behind, Barracks Rd, High Wycombe. c 1969
Former main entrance building of High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital in foreground (empty), with Phase one of the General Hospital behind. Sign states 'Outpatients Entrance now through Main Hospital Entrance Queen Alexandra Road.'

mentions.ne_span: High Wycombe and District War Memorial Hospital

text:
Alec Dean in front of a shed, using an axe to roughly shape a chair leg in Hampden Woods, Great Hampden. December 1949
Alec Dean using an axe to roughly shape a chair leg using a tree stump as a workbench surrounded by shavings. Behind him is a shed and two bicycles are propped up. A pole leads into the shed, part of the pole-lathe used to turn the chair legs. Other tools lay on the ground. Also seen on BFP05708 and BFP05540

Looking N, a view of John and Joan Gore cutting the cake at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
John Gore, Hon. Sec.of High Wycombe Society, and Joan Gore cut the cake at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society. They are watched by Chairman Roger Lawson right, and by Eric Alexander. Other members in background.

Looking N/NW, a view of the W end of S side of the main building of the General Hospital, Queen Alexandra Rd, High Wycombe. early 1970's
View of the W end of S side of main building of Wycombe General Hospital with bridge linking it to later construction. Newland multi-storey car park seen in background.

Looking W at front of Wycombe Museum, a view of F.Alexander and R.Swains at the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Frances Alexander and Ronald Swains recalling Jack Scruton's appearance before a Parliamentary committee, at a party to celebrate the 25th anniversary of the High Wycombe Society. The party was held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum.

From NW, a view to the SE side of Church St near cross roads, showing the shops in Lane End. 1960's
View of shops on SE side of Church St near the crossroads. The shops of John Carr and Druces are shown with cars standing outside. A road leads off left behind a cottage.

Looking N, a view of the S side of the main Hospital building, with linking bridge. Queen Alexandra Rd, High Wycombe. early 1970's
View of the Southern side of main building of Wycombe General Hospital with bridge linking it to later construction.

Looking SW, a view of an exhibition of period household utensils in the kitchen at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1995
Exhibition of household utensils in the kitchen of Wycombe Museum.

Detail view of a cake made by Diana Stone for the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society. Probably at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
A decorated cake made by Diana Stone for the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum.

Looking S, a view of the construction site at the General Hospital showing start of Phase 3, Queen Alexandra Rd, High Wycombe. 1971
View of construction site at Wycombe General Hospital showing roof of Phase 2, X-ray and outpatients, in foreground and the beginnings of Phase 3, maternity, obstetrics, gynaecology and paediatrics. Accommodation blocks, completed in 1964, top right. Marlow Hill and Wycombe Abbey School beyond top left.

Owen Dean left and Alec Dean right using a cross-cut saw to cut tree trunks into butts in Hampden Woods, Great Hampden. December 1949
Owen Dean left and Alec Dean right using a cross-cut saw to cut beech tree trunks into butts in Hampden Woods. Also seen on BFP05705

Looking NE, a view from the construction site of the General Hospital with Wycombe Abbey School beyond. Marlow Hill, High Wycombe. early 1970's
View from construction site of Wycombe General Hospital with buildings of later phase in foreground. Centre shows buildings of Wycombe Abbey School with boarding houses on Marlow Hill to the fore and Wycombe Abbey in front of trees. Abbey Way seen top left.

A view of part of a new display of chairs after remodelling of the exhibition area in Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
A new display of chairs after remodelling of exhibition area of Wycombe Museum. Two chairs shown, one with a cane seat. One is smaller, a traveller's sample of a cane folding chair. Information boards show other chair designs. There is a poster for J. Elliott and Son of Desborough Rd and Shaftesbury St High Wycombe. Another angle of MHW02445

Detail view of a cake made by Diana Stone for the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society. Probably at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. June 1993
Detailed view of a decorated cake made by Diana Stone for the 25th anniversary party of the High Wycombe Society held in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum.

Looking S from nr the junction of Marlow Hill/Queen Alexandra Rd, a model of new hospital building with nurses' accommodation. off Marlow Hill, High Wycombe. early 1960's
Elevated view of a model of new hospital building and car park with nurses' accommodation in background top right. Marlow Hill on left, Queen Alexandra Rd bottom right and Barracks Rd. running from Marlow Hill in front of accommodation block.

Looking NW, an exterior view of High Wycombe Cottage Hospital and gardens in Priory Rd, High Wycombe. c 1900?
Exterior view of High Wycombe Cottage Hospital and gardens with ivy covered veranda.

Louise Perrin receiving a framed photograph at her farewell party in the Education Room of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1999
Louise Perrin, Documentation Assistant at Wycombe Museum, being presented with a framed photograph at her farewell party held in the Education Room at the Museum. From left to right, John Smithson, John Rutland, Richard Bird, Keith Wilkins, Leslie Dandy, Mary Dandy, Louise Perrin and Victoria Wood. Same event seen on MHW02208 to 02210

The Dean brothers using an axe to roughly shape chair legs in front of their workshop in Hampden Woods, Great Hampden. December 1949
In Hampden Woods, Owen Dean left working with his brother Alec right, using an axe to roughly shape chair legs using tree stumps as a workbench. Behind them stands the workshop and the external part of the pole lathe. Two piles of roughly shaped legs stand by the men. Also seen on BFP05710

Looking NE from S of Barracks Rd, an elevated view of a model of new hospital building and nurses' accommodation, off Marlow Hill, High Wycombe. early 1960's
Model of new hospital building. Nurses' accommodation in foreground south of Barracks Rd. Marlow Hill on top right and Queen Alexandra Rd. runs behind the main block from right to left.

Twenty-seven chairs, a tilt top table and a cupboard with inlaid work in a storage room at Wycombe Museum post refurbishment of the Museum.

Eric Knowles, Annabel Langley and Felicity Kane n a refurbished gallery at the Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. March 1999
Eric Knowles an antique expert from the Antiques Roadshow television programme, with Annabel Langley and Felicity Kane when he came to officially open the refurbished galleries in Wycombe Museum. The two girls had their collection of Beanie Babies on display in 'Your Case' which was a display cabinet for the public to show their own collections.

A display of woodworking tools hanging on the wall and on a well-used workbench at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
A display of woodworking tools hanging on the wall and on a well-used workbench. Left, resting against the bench, splats for wheel-back chairs. Right, a finished chair and a window.

Looking NW to Education Room, a view of refurbishment of the Education Room of Wycombe Museum, with adjacent building. Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990
Refurbishment of Education Room of Wycombe Museum with brick and flint walls to raised flower beds. Adjacent to an older weather-boarded building. A machine stands in the yard and a skip is in bottom right. In the background houses in The Haystacks. Renovation work also seen on MHW02193 to 02202

Looking W, a view of the newly refurbished Education Room, with brick and flint walls to raised beds. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990
Newly refurbished Education Room of Wycombe Museum with brick and flint walls to raised flower beds. A machine stands in the yard and a skip is in bottom left. Renovation work also seen on MHW02193 to 02202

Looking W in Red Lion Yard, a view of cottages (nos 6-7) in Red Lion Yard and the rear of no 16 in St Mary St, High Wycombe. c 1935
Looking down into yard of Red Lion Public house on E. of St Mary St. cottages at the time of the Slum Clearance. Covered cart with shafts up. Washing on line. St.Mary Street Front of nos. 6-7 Red Lion Yard Rear of no. 16 St. Mary Street [md] Wider view of MHW02242

View of a metal plate used to help bend the backs of Windsor bow back chairs. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990's
A metal plate with rows of holes used to help in the bending of wood (usually yew) to make the backs of Windsor bow back chairs. See photos of Jack Goodchild using one [md]. Seen possibly outside the Education Room in Wycombe Museum.

Looking NE towards the crossroads, a view of the scene following an accident outside the Post Office, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. March 1982
From an upper Library window, looking towards junction of Queen Victoria Rd High St Crendon St and Easton St following an accident. An articulated lorry overturned outside the Post Office after brake failure at the junction of Totteridge Rd and Amersham Hill. Lorry driver Robert Crompton and car driver Clifford Dawkins unhurt. A police car on the left. Behind the Post Office, left Britannic Assurance, Terry's Gents Hairdresser and Connells Estate Agents. Vera Williams Dress shop on far corner. Just visible is the roof of Union Baptist Church.

A view of the Mayors' room - a display of paintings, pictures, regalia and furniture in the Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1988
The Mayors' Room in Wycombe Museum with paintings of two Mayors, a Master's Chair and the Warden's Chair of a Company or Guild, the Mace Bearer's Uniform, the Chepping Wycombe Mace, a globe and other posters and pictures.

A display showing woodworking tools and the parts of a Windsor chair, part of an exhibition called The Country Chair. location unknown. date unknown
A display stand showing a selection of bit braces and other woodworking tools and the constituent parts of a Windsor chair. Left two Windsor chairs. This is the reverse of the display seen on MHW02484. Another view on MHW02486. Preparations for an exhibition entitled The Country Chair.

Looking E, an elevated view of crowds looking at an articulated lorry overturned outside the Post Office, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe, March 1982
From an upper Library window, crowds looking at an articulated lorry overturned outside the Post Office after brake failure at the junction of Totteridge Rd and Amersham Hill. Lorry driver Robert Crompton and car driver Clifford Dawkins unhurt. A police car on the left. In the background the Post office and left Britannic Assurance, Terry's Gents. Hairdresser and Connells Estate Agents.

Eric Knowles, Annabel Langley and Felicity Kane n a refurbished gallery at the Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. March 1999
Eric Knowles an antique expert from the Antiques Roadshow television programme, with Annabel Langley and Felicity Kane when he came to officially open the refurbished galleries in Wycombe Museum. The two girls had their collection of Beanie Babies on display in 'Your Case' which was a display cabinet for the public to show their own collections.

Looking N from front door of Museum, a view of the hall and reception desk post-refurbishment. Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
Entrance hall of Museum with reception desk post-refurbishment. [md] Albert Ivermee, a Museum volunteer, stands next to the desk and another man is working behind. On the desk and on the shelves behind are items for sale.

Looking NE from upper floor of Library, a view of a fire engine and police car attending an overturned lorry in Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. March 1982
A fire engine and police car attending an accident outside the Post Office. An articulated lorry overturned after brake failure at the junction of Totteridge Rd and Amersham Hill. Lorry driver Robert Crompton and car driver Clifford Dawkins were unhurt. A crowd looks on. Photograph taken from first floor of Wycombe Library. Post Office in background. To the left Britannic Assurance and Terrys Gents Hairdresser. Same event on RHW02336 - 02347

Looking W in Red Lion Yard, a view of cottages (nos 6-7) in Red Lion Yard and the rear of nos 16-17 in St Mary St, High Wycombe. c 1935
Looking down into yard of Red Lion Public house on E. of St Mary St. cottages at the time of the Slum Clearance. Covered cart with shafts up and horse tethered . Washing on line. St Mary Street Front of nos 6-7 Red Lion Yard Rear of nos. 16-17 St. Mary Street [md] Part of evidence gathered for slum clearance. Also on RHW45003

From E. to front of building at rear of Wycombe Museum, exterior refurbishment of buildings to the rear of the Museum, Priory Ave. High Wycombe, 1990.
Exterior refurbishment of buildings to the rear of Wycombe Museum. [md] The refurbished building is used as the Education Room [2006] To the right is a wooden building.

Looking E from an upper Library window, a view of a fire engine and police cars attending an accident outside the Post Office, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. March 1982
From an upper Library window, a fire engine and police cars attending an accident outside the Post Office. An articulated lorry overturned outside the Post Office after brake failure at the junction of Totteridge Rd. and Amersham Hill. Lorry driver Robert Crompton and car driver Clifford Dawkins unhurt. A small crowd looks on.

Two display panels entitled The Country Chair, preparations for an unknown exhibition. location unknown. date unknown.
Two display panels on a stand entitled The Country Chair, preparations for an unknown exhibition. On the left are photographs and information about the bodgers. On the right information about chair manufacture .Displayed behind the panels are three chairs. Other views on MHW02485/6

Looking N in the gardens of the Museum at the entrance, John Gore cuts a cake celebrating 25 years of the H.W.Society. Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
John Gore, Hon. Sec. of the High Wycombe Society, and Mrs Joan Gore cut a cake to celebrate 25 years of the Society in the gardens of Wycombe Museum. To the right stands Roger Lawson, the Chairman, and on the left Eric Alexander looks on. There is a banner to the right and balloons to the left.

A yard outside the workshop of Mr White with chair legs stacked against the wall and roughly shaped wood. Beacons Bottom, nr Stokenchurch. late 1930's
Yard outside the workshop of Mr White. Chair legs are stacked against the wall also wood roughly cut to shape for later working. To the right a smaller hut with a pile of cut wood. in front. The wooden, thatched building has a power transformer on the right with a pole adjacent. Other views of the workshop on MHW02330 - 02333

Mayor and Mayoress, Mr and Mrs McLellan with Sir John and Mrs Hall at the Old People's Workshop, 84a, Easton St, High Wycombe. Dec 1963
The Mayor and Mayoress, Mr and Mrs T. McLellan with Sir John and Mrs Hall hand round Christmas cake at a party for members of the Old People's Workshop in Easton St. Streamers decorate the walls. Report in Bucks Free Press Saturday December 28th 1963. Same picture RHW02148. Same event RHW02141 and 02147

Workshop of Mr White, a wooden building with thatched roof, with logs piled in the yard. Beacons Bottom, nr Stokenchurch. c 1930
Workshop of Mr White, a wooden building with thatched roof. Tree trunks wait to be cut. On the wall a poster advertises a Benefit Whist Drive to be held in the Church Hall of St Francis on Friday October 31st. Other views of the workshop on MHW02330 02331 - 02334

An interior view of a corner of a room during refurbishment at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990
An interior view of a corner of a room in Wycombe Museum during refurbishment.

Inside a marquee, a view of a display by Wycombe Local History and Chair Museum at Wycombe Show, the Rye, High Wycombe. Sept 1993
Among others, a display by Wycombe Local History and Chair Museum at Wycombe Show. Three panels have photographs and text. Two tables display artifacts, leaflets and souvenirs to buy.

mentions.ne_span: Wycombe Local History and Chair Museum
Wycombe Local History and Chair Museum

text:
Looking SE in front of the Museum, a group of school children dressed as evacuees from World War II, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1970's
A group of school children dressed as World War II evacuees in the gardens of Wycombe Museum, with their teacher. One girl is reading aloud.

Pensioners receiving tins of biscuits at a Christmas party at the Old People's Workshop in 84a, Easton St, High Wycombe. c 1960?
Pensioners receiving tins of biscuits at a Christmas party for members of the Old People's Workshop in Easton St. Some are wearing party hats and there are crackers on the tables.

A man using a foot powered pole lathe in a modern setting. location unknown. date unknown
A young man works a foot powered pole lathe. The lathe appears to be an 'engineered' reconstruction of a traditional pole-lathe, being made of prepared wood rather than branches.

Looking NW from the drive, the front of Wycombe Museum (formerly Castle Hill House) with an iron lamp-post in foreground. Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1995
The front of Wycombe Museum, formerly Castle Hill House, seen from the drive. Two benches stand in front of the building. An iron lamppost stands at junction of drive and footpath.

An exhibition of Indian Art with artists and dignitaries present. An upper gallery in Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1992
At an exhibition of Indian Art held in the upper galleries of Wycombe Museum, artists and dignitaries including Pam Priestley, a District Councillor, middle. Same event on MHW02175 and 02232

A display of bodger's tools including a pole lathe, pit saw, shave horse and a chair, seen in Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990
A display of bodger's tools including a pole lathe, a pit saw and a shave horse together with a Windsor chair seen in Wycombe Museum. The background is an enlarged photograph of a wood with two smaller photographs. One of a man bending a chair back, the other of a woodworker making a spoke back. Also seen on MHW02515

Looking N, a view of P. Crouch on a windsurfer with N. Wyatt Spratt, in the grounds of the Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. c 1990
Philip Crouch posed on a windsurfer with Neridah Wyatt Spratt helping, in the front garden of the Museum. Same event on MHW02180, 02181, 02183 and 02184

Paintings and boxes in a storage room with shelving and a chair. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. late 1980's?
Paintings and boxes seen in a storage room in Wycombe Museum with shelving and a chair. Also seen on MHW02520

A man, probably Mr White, turning a chair leg on a wheel lathe converted from a pole lathe. Beacons Bottom, nr Stokenchurch. 1930's
A man, probably Mr White, turning a chair leg on a wheel lathe converted from a pole lathe in a workshop.

Looking S from the interior of Wycombe Museum, a view of the Red Lion being lifted through an upper window. Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1995
Catalogued by Jame Rattue as the Red Lion from the hotel of the same name in the High St, being raised through an upper window. Originally catalogued as an exhibit for the Dinosaur Exhibition 1994 being lifted through a window. [md] A painting hangs on the left wall.

Three women and two men at a Christmas Party, probably at the Old People's Workshop, 84a Easton St, High Wycombe. 1960's?
Three women and two men sitting at the top table(?) at a Christmas Party, probably one held for pensioners at the Old People's Workshop at Easton St

Looking N, a view of P. Crouch on a windsurfer with N. Wyatt Spratt, in the grounds of the Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. c 1990
Philip Crouch posed on a windsurfer in the front garden of the Museum with Neridah Wyatt Spratt standing beside. She is holding a magazine entitled Museums. Same event on MHW02180 and 02182-4

Interior view, probably of the basement prior to refurbishment. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. late 1980's?
Interior view, probably of the basement prior to refurbishment. Wycombe Museum

Looking N inside the Guildhall, a view of part of an exhibition entitled 'Our House', showing household furniture from the 1950s. High St, High Wycombe. 1992
Part of an exhibition in the main room of the Guildhall. The exhibition entitled 'Our House' includes a display of household furniture from 1950s. At the far end is the dais and on the right windows overlooking the High St.

Mrs Steer pins a button hole on Pop Parkin at his birthday party at the Old People's Workshop in 84a, Easton St, High Wycombe. 1960's?
Mrs Steer pinning a button hole on Pop Parkin at a party to celebrate his birthday at the Old People's Workshop in Easton St. Mrs Collier stands behind. A present is on the table in the foreground. Same event on RHW02165

Looking NW from the drive, the front of Wycombe Museum (formerly Castle Hill House) with an iron lamp-post in foreground. Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1995
The front of Wycombe Museum, formerly Castle Hill House, seen from the drive. Two benches stand in front of the building. In the foreground is an iron lamppost.

A view of a timber-framed wall with lath and plaster and brick wall adjacent, revealed during refurbishment at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990
Timber framed wall with lath and plaster and brick wall adjacent seen during refurbishment of buildings at Wycombe Museum.

Looking N, a view of P. Crouch on a windsurfer with N. Wyatt Spratt, in the grounds of the Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. c 1990
Philip Crouch posed on a windsurfer in the front garden of the Museum with Neridah Wyatt Spratt standing beside. She is holding a copy of Museums magazine. Same event on MHW02180-3

Men and women working in the Old People's Workshop in 84a Easton St, High Wycombe. early 1960's
Men and women working in the Old People's Workshop in Easton St.

Looking S, a view of a display entitled 'Refurbishment of the Outbuildings'. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. early 1990's
Three panels with a display of text and plans entitled Refurbishment of the Outbuildings. The outbuildings at the rear of the Museum, including the former garage, were refurbished to include the new Education Room. Wycombe Museum was formerly Castle Hill House. From the window there is a view of the front lawn.

View of a model of a set of six Windsor dining chairs and two carvers around a table. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990
A model of a set of six Windsor dining chairs and two carvers around a table in Wycombe Museum.

A man working in a yard outside Mr White's workshop, splitting a butt with beetle and wedge axe. Beacons Bottom, nr Stokenchurch. about 1930
A man working outside Mr White's workshop. The long wooden building is thatched. In the yard are tree trunks waiting to be cut. On the wall a poster advertises a Benefit Whist Drive to be held in the Church Hall of St Francis on Friday October 31st. Splitting a butt with beetle and wedge axe, dog saw behind [md] Other views of the workshop on MHW02330 and 02332 - 02333

Sgt.A Legge with Mrs Shrimpton and Mr Fuller holding a large cake at the Old People's Workshop, 84a Easton St, High Wycombe. April 1960
Sgt. A. Legge in military uniform holds a large decorated cake with Mrs Shrimpton and Mr Fuller on either side at the Old People's Workshop in Easton St.

Looking N across lawns, view of deckchair with painted chair design, part of a larger exhibition at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1991
On the lawn in front of Wycombe Museum, a deckchair painted with a chair design, part of a larger exhibition of deck-chairs. Seven others behind. Two benches stand in front of the Museum, formerly Castle Hill House. This exhibition seen on MHW02503 - 02509 and MHW02354 - 02362

Eric Knowles and Ted Collins (Mayor) with others at the opening of an exhibition at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1992?
Eric Knowles, an expert from the Antiques Roadshow programme, and Ted Collins Mayor with others at the opening of an exhibition. Panels entitled Timeline and Coming to Live hang on the wall behind.

Looking N, a view of Philip Crouch on a windsurfer in the grounds of the Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. c 1990
Philip Crouch posed on a windsurfer in the front garden of the Museum. Same event on MHW02180-2 and 02184

Pensioners watch conjuring tricks at a Christmas party at the Old People's Workshop in 84a, Easton St, High Wycombe. 1960's?
Pensioners watch an elderly man performing conjuring tricks at a Christmas party at the Old People's Workshop in Easton St. The walls are decorated with streamers and Christmas cards. Same event on RHW02159 and RHW02162

A stand displaying clothing etc. made by members of the Old People's Workshop in Easton St. Probably at the District Show, The Rye, High Wycombe, Sept 1963
Probably taken at the High Wycombe District Show on the Rye, a stand displaying articles of clothing made by members of the Old People's Workshop in Easton St. Mrs B. Place the Secretary is also there.

Looking N across the lawns, a view of thirteen deck-chairs, part of a larger display at Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1991
On the lawns in front of Wycombe Museum, thirteen deck-chairs, part of a larger exhibition, the canvases decorated with individual designs. Three benches stand in front of the Museum, formerly Castle Hill House, and a notice board in the porch. Behind.left, houses in The Haystacks. This exhibition seen on MHW02503 - 02509 and MHW02354 - 02362

John and Nancy Hall and the Mayoress with pensioners at a Christmas Party, Old People's Workshop, 84a Easton St, High Wycombe. early 1960's?
Sir John Hall, Nancy Hall and the Mayoress talk to pensioners at a Christmas party held at the Old People's Workshop at Easton St. The walls and tables have been decorated.

View of a corner of a room with a small window overlooking gardens, at the Wycombe Museum prior to refurbishment. Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990
Interior museum display and storage pre-refurbishment. [md] Corner of a room with a small window overlooking gardens. A crate stands on the floor.

A view of the workshop of Mr White in a derelict state. Beacons Bottom, nr Stokenchurch. date unknown.
Mr White's workshop in a derelict state. The roof is thatched, it has two small windows and a door on the left. Overhead power-transformer just seen on right. Also seen on RHW12241 Other views on MHW02331 - 02333

An interior view of the cellars or basement of garage before refurbishment. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. late 1980's?
The cellars under Wycombe Museum with white painted brick wall and shelving. There is an electricity socket and right a wooden and metal cupboard or possibly a heater. Interior of garage before refurbishment[md]

Men and women gathered for a Christmas party at the Old People's Workshop at 84a, Easton St, High Wycombe. 1964
Men and women gathered for a Christmas party at the Old People's Workshop at Easton St. sitting around decorated tables.

View of an exhibition room with display case, and an enlarged photograph (mural) of a beech wood; part of a display in Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
An exhibition room in Wycombe Museum with a display case to the left. Through the doorway, another room with an enlarged photograph (mural) of a beech wood in Autumn Also seen on MHW02475

Mrs Robinson and Miss Janes and others at the Old People's Workshop at 84a, Easton St, High Wycombe. c 1963
Mrs Robinson and Miss Janes at the Old People's Workshop at 84a Easton St. Mrs Robinson is packing vacuum cleaner 'Disposall' bags for Hoover. Others are seen working in the background

A display of artifacts and a painting of the Resurrection of Lazarus in the Mayors' Room, Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1988
A display of artifacts in the Mayors' Room at Wycombe Museum including a painting of The Resurrection of Lazarus, measures marked in bushels, tripod scales, a flag of the Reunion? Association 1915-19 Salonika, a bell, a carving of a man with a swan and pictures.

View of a large stone snail in the gardens of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
A large stone snail in the gardens at the front of Wycombe Museum. The photograph was taken at the party to celebrate 25 years of the High Wycombe Society. Three members of the Society stand behind.

Members of Wycombe Wesleyans Football Club, 1925-26 posed in their kit. location unknown. 1926
Members of Wycombe Wesleyans Football Club, 1925-26 posed in their kit. For players' names etc see also RHW06457

An interior view of the cellars or basement of garage before refurbishment. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. late 1980's?
The cellars under Wycombe Museum with white painted brick wall and wooden table. There is an electric socket and wire. Left a support seen on MHW02374/5 Interior of garage before refurbishment[md]

Looking NE towards the S face of Wycombe Museum, a view of the grounds, post restoration. Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990's?
Museum gardens in summer, post restoration [md] The gardens are shown with summer bedding. To the right of the entrance panels hang on the outside wall perhaps part of, or advertising, an exhibition. A pile of stones is stacked beneath a window.

Presentation by Mrs Parry-Jones to Mr and Mrs James Farnes at the Old People's Workshop, Easton St, High Wycombe. March 1960
Mrs Parry-Jones making a presentation to Mr and Mrs James Farnes for their Golden Wedding which was on Tuesday March 1st. This presentation was at the Old People's Workshop in Easton St, which Mr Farnes attends. For more details see the Bucks Free Press for Friday March 4th 1960.

A display of chair-making tools. location uncertain, possibly the old Museum, Queen Victoria Rd, High Wycombe. date unknown
Chair making tools arranged in a display in a Museum Skirting/door etc suggest the former museum, currently (2006) the Reference Library, but not in 1991! (HDC)

Men and women gathered for a Christmas party at the Old People's Workshop at 84a, Easton St, High Wycombe. 1964
Men and women gathered for a Christmas party at the Old People's Workshop at Easton St. sitting around decorated tables.

View of an enlarged photograph (mural) of a beech wood in Autumn, part of an interior display in Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
Seen through a doorway, an interior display in Wycombe Museum showing an enlarged photograph (mural) of a beech wood in Autumn. Left a display case. Also seen on MHW02476

Pop Parkin with his presents at a party to celebrate his birthday at the Old People's Workshop in 84a, Easton St, High Wycombe. 1960's?
Pop Parkin seen holding his presents at a party to celebrate his birthday at the Old People's Workshop in Easton St. Other pensioners look on. Same event on RHW02164

Sir John Hall and Nancy Hall visiting a Christmas Party at the Old People's Workshop, 84a Easton St, High Wycombe. early 1960's
Sir John Hall, the local Member of Parliament, and his wife Nancy next to him, visiting a Christmas party at the Old People's Workshop in Easton St.Two women are seen talking to the old people seated around the tables which have Christmas decorations.

View of a corner of a room with a window overlooking gardens and sloping roof. The Wycombe Museum prior to refurbishment. Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990
Interior museum display and storage pre-refurbishment. [md] Corner of a room in Wycombe Museum with a window overlooking gardens and a sloping roof.

In the playground of Castlefield School, members of Copyground and Castlefield Social Club enjoying a fete. Starling Rd, Castlefield, High Wycombe, late 1950's
Members of Copyground and Castlefield Social Club enjoying a fete held at Castlefield School. Seen from second left Graham Smith, Ernest Smith, Valerie Ives, Lyn Stevens, Linda Dobbs and Leslie Cave.

View of cattle drinking in the pond before the Royal Oak PH at Bovingdon Green, nr Marlow. 1930's?
View of cattle drinking in the pond before the Royal Oak PH at Bovingdon Green

Looking N. from a tent in gardens of Wycombe Museum, a clarinetist at the 25th anniversary of the High Wycombe Society, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
A clarinetist, part of a five man jazz group, performing inside a marquee set up on the front lawns of Wycombe Museum. This was part of the 25th anniversary celebrations for the High Wycombe Society. At left, a person in a kilt. Same event on MHW02382-87, MHW02211-13, MHW02188

A view of a wooden door, set in a white painted brick wall, possibly in the scullery of Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. late 1980's?
Interior view in Wycombe Museum with white painted brick wall with wooden door. There is an electric socket and wires. Possibly in the scullery.

Pop Parkin with Mrs Collier and Mrs Steer at his birthday party at the Old People's Workshop in 84a, Easton St, High Wycombe. 1960's?
Pop Parkin at a birthday party arranged for him at the Old People's Workshop in Easton St. Mrs Collier stands on the left and Mrs Steer on the right. Same event on RHW02161

Part of an interior display in Wycombe Museum, featuring an enlarged photograph of woodland. Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
A display in Wycombe Museum featuring an enlarged photograph of woodland. Through the doorway is the reception area, with shelving displaying books. Another view of MHW02477

Looking N in the main room, P. Crouch and N. Wyatt Spratt and another at an exhibition in the Guildhall, High St, High Wycombe. August 1990
Philip Crouch, Neridah Wyatt Spratt and a man by an early bicycle, part of an exhibition in the Guildhall. The exhibition had the title Collective Memories. [md]

Looking W in playground of Mill End Rd School, Ken Stanners posed with other boys for a school photograph. Mill End Rd, High Wycombe. 1950's
Group of forty-three boys posed in playground of Mill End Rd. School. Ken Stanners first left on top standing taller.

Looking E across the gardens, a display of sixteen deckchairs, the canvases with individual designs. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1991
On the lawn in front Wycombe Museum, a display of sixteen deckchairs, the canvases decorated with individual designs. The Museum, formerly Castle Hill House, on the left with four benches in front. This exhibition on MHW02354 - 02362

John and Nancy Hall, and the Mayor and Mayoress with pensioners at a Christmas Party, Old People's Workshop, 84a Easton St, High Wycombe. 1963
Sir John Hall, the local M.P. with Mrs Nancy Hall, Thomas McLellan the Mayor and the Mayoress with a group of pensioners at a Christmas Party held at the Old People's Workshop at Easton St. The walls and tables have been decorated.

View of a corner of a room with a window, filled in fireplace and door. The Wycombe Museum prior to refurbishment. Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1990
Interior museum display and storage pre-refurbishment. [md] Room in Museum being refurbished with materials standing on the floor and on a stepladder. On the left a spade rests against a filled in fireplace and a door is in the corner. Through the window part of the building with scaffolding can be seen.

Castlefield Wives' Group presenting a cheque to Andrew Harris and Mr. Powel. In High Wycombe Hospital, Queen Alexandra Rd, High Wycombe. Aug 1978
Castlefield Wives Group at Wycombe Hospital presenting a cheque for £100. From left to right Valerie Stanners, Andrew Harris, Mr Powel, Grace Turner, Pauline Baker

a view of Alderman N.W. Gurney, (Chairman of BCC) and other officials at the official opening of Branch Library, Reynolds Rd, Beaconsfield. March 1957
Alderman N.W.Gurney Chairman of Bucks. County Council, speaking at the official opening of the Beaconsfield Branch Library. To his left Alderman R.Taylor Chairman of the Library Committee, Councillor B.E.Wisker Chairman of Beaconsfield Urban District Council, Councillor C.W.E.Whishand and Miss Gwen Jones County Librarian. The Library, designed by the County Architect F.B.Pooley, was the County Council's first post-war library.

John Hall M.P. (right) watching men and women at work in the Old People's Workshop at 84a, Easton St, High Wycombe. c 1963
Men and women working at the Old People's Workshop in Easton St. One of the jobs was packing disposable vacuum cleaner bags for Hoover.

Pam Priestley and a man, with a woman (possibly the artist) at an Indian Exhibition in Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1992
Pam Priestley and a man talking to a woman in a sari, possibly the artist, at an Indian Exhibition held in Wycombe Museum.

A man entertains pensioners with conjuring tricks at a Christmas party at the Old People's Workshop in 84a Easton St, High Wycombe. 1960's?
An elderly man entertaining pensioners with conjuring tricks at a Christmas party at the Old People's Workshop in Easton St. The walls are decorated with streamers and Christmas cards. Same event on RHW02159 and RHW02163

Nancy Hall, the Mayoress, Mrs Gibb and Mrs Jeffries at a Christmas Party at the Old People's Workshop, 84a Easton St, High Wycombe. 1963
Mrs Nancy Hall, wife of the Member of Parliament and the Mayoress Mrs P. McLennan pose with Mrs Gibb and Mrs Jeffries at the Christmas Party held at the Old People's Workshop at Easton St.

Part of an interior display in Wycombe Museum, featuring an enlarged photograph of woodland. Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1994
A display in Wycombe Museum featuring an enlarged photograph of woodland. Through the doorway is the reception area, with shelving displaying books. Another view of MHW02478

A view of Cllr. B.E.Wisker Chair of Beaconsfield U.D.C.and others at the official opening of the Branch Library, Reynolds Rd, Beaconsfield. March 1957
At the official opening of Beaconsfield Branch Library from left Alderman N.W.Gurney Chairman of Bucks. County Council, Alderman R.Taylor Chairman of the Library Committee, Councillor B.E.Wisker Chairman of Beaconsfield Urban District Council speaking, Councillor C.W.E.Whishand and Miss Gwen Jones County Librarian. The Library, designed by the County Architect F.B.Pooley, was the County Council's first post-war library.

Looking E across the gardens, a display of sixteen deckchairs, the canvases with individual designs. Wycombe Museum, Priory Ave, High Wycombe. 1991
On the lawn in front Wycombe Museum, a display of sixteen deckchairs, the canvases decorated with individual designs. The Museum, formerly Castle Hill House, on the left with four benches in front. This exhibition on MHW02354 - 02362

Julie Massey and Peter Cartwright at an exhibition of household furniture of the 1950s, held in the Guildhall, High St, High Wycombe. Aug 1992
